WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:04.590 --> 00:00:05.830
[MAN SPEAKS SARDAUKAR]

2
00:00:13.100 --> 00:00:14.590
[SLOW DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

3
00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:22.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

4
00:00:41.920 --> 00:00:44.080
[RHYTHMIC THUMPING MUSIC PLAYING]

5
00:00:56.310 --> 00:00:58.420
[GIRL IN ENGLISH]
<i>My planet Arrakis is so beautiful</i>

6
00:00:58.520 --> 00:00:59.970
<i>when the sun is low.</i>

7
00:01:03.440 --> 00:01:05.100
<i>Rolling over the sands...</i>

8
00:01:06.190 --> 00:01:08.400
<i>you can see spice in the air.</i>

9
00:01:14.410 --> 00:01:16.150
[INHUMAN GROWL]

10
00:01:21.620 --> 00:01:25.210
<i>At nightfall. the spice harvesters land.</i>

11
00:01:26.710 --> 00:01:30.380
<i>The outsiders race against time
to avoid the heat of the day.</i>

12
00:01:35.140 --> 00:01:37.170
[THUMPING MUSIC TEMPO INCREASING]

13
00:01:40.480 --> 00:01:43.390
<i>They ravage our lands
in front of our eyes.</i>

14
00:01:44.440 --> 00:01:47.400
<i>Their cruelty to my people
is all I've known.</i>

15
00:01:48.190 --> 00:01:50.150
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

16
00:01:52.950 --> 00:01:55.310
<i>These outsiders. the Harkonnens.</i>

17
00:01:55.410 --> 00:01:57.400
<i>came long before I was born.</i>

18
00:01:57.580 --> 00:01:59.440
<i>By controlling spice production.</i>

19
00:01:59.540 --> 00:02:01.320
<i>they became obscenely rich.</i>

20
00:02:01.660 --> 00:02:03.450
<i>Richer than the Emperor himself.</i>

21
00:02:05.250 --> 00:02:06.330
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

22
00:02:21.560 --> 00:02:23.220
- [STABS]
- [MAN SCREAMING]

23
00:02:25.270 --> 00:02:26.560
[GUNSHOT]

24
00:02:31.690 --> 00:02:33.150
[EXPLOSIONS]

25
00:02:37.370 --> 00:02:38.400
[SCREAMING]

26
00:02:46.000 --> 00:02:49.160
<i>Our warriors couldn't free
Arrakis from the Harkonnens.</i>

27
00:02:49.420 --> 00:02:50.660
<i>but one day.</i>

28
00:02:50.750 --> 00:02:53.790
<i>by Imperial decree. they were gone.</i>

29
00:03:00.970 --> 00:03:03.180
<i>Why did the Emperor choose this path?</i>

30
00:03:04.730 --> 00:03:06.970
<i>And who will our next oppressors be?</i>

31
00:03:16.530 --> 00:03:18.150
[INHALES DEEPLY]

32
00:03:27.540 --> 00:03:29.370
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

33
00:03:44.730 --> 00:03:46.510
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

34
00:03:58.410 --> 00:03:59.990
[LADY JESSICA]
It's good you're up early.

35
00:04:01.660 --> 00:04:02.820
Your father wants you in full dress

36
00:04:02.910 --> 00:04:04.490
before the Emperor's Herald arrives.

37
00:04:05.410 --> 00:04:06.650
Full dress?

38
00:04:07.790 --> 00:04:08.750
Military?

39
00:04:09.460 --> 00:04:11.370
- Ceremonial.
- [PAUL SIGHS]

40
00:04:12.130 --> 00:04:13.330
Why do we have to go
through all this

41
00:04:13.420 --> 00:04:14.580
when it's already been decided?

42
00:04:16.210 --> 00:04:17.250
Ceremony.

43
00:04:17.970 --> 00:04:18.960
Mm.

44
00:04:19.890 --> 00:04:20.800
Thank you.

45
00:04:22.720 --> 00:04:24.510
If you want it. make me give it to you.

46
00:04:26.020 --> 00:04:26.970
Use the Voice.

47
00:04:27.730 --> 00:04:28.840
Mom. I just woke up.

48
00:04:37.150 --> 00:04:38.270
Give me the water.

49
00:04:39.400 --> 00:04:41.240
The glass can't hear you.
Command me.

50
00:04:59.260 --> 00:05:01.370
[WIND CHIMES TINKLING]

51
00:05:09.100 --> 00:05:10.640
[DISTORTED VOICE] Give me the water.

52
00:05:17.650 --> 00:05:19.110
[WIND CHIMES STOPS TINKLING]

53
00:05:23.320 --> 00:05:24.280
Almost.

54
00:05:24.870 --> 00:05:25.860
[NORMAL VOICE] Almost?

55
00:05:26.370 --> 00:05:28.610
Bene Gesserit skills
take years to learn. Paul.

56
00:05:28.700 --> 00:05:30.910
- [PAUL] Mm-hmm.
- You look tired.

57
00:05:32.250 --> 00:05:33.280
More dreams?

58
00:05:39.340 --> 00:05:40.420
No.

59
00:05:43.510 --> 00:05:44.970
[NARRATOR OVER SPEAKERS]
<i>Extreme temperatures</i>

60
00:05:45.050 --> 00:05:46.790
<i>and treacherous weather events</i>

61
00:05:46.970 --> 00:05:50.560
<i>make life outside the cities
of Arrakis truly hostile.</i>

62
00:05:50.730 --> 00:05:52.510
<i>with sandstorms powerful enough</i>

63
00:05:52.600 --> 00:05:53.840
<i>to cut through metal.</i>

64
00:05:54.440 --> 00:05:57.020
<i>Only the native tribes
known as the Fremen</i>

65
00:05:57.190 --> 00:05:59.650
<i>have adapted well enough to survive.</i>

66
00:06:01.190 --> 00:06:04.440
<i>Preferring to inhabit
the remotest regions of Arrakis.</i>

67
00:06:05.620 --> 00:06:07.230
<i>the Fremen share the deep desert</i>

68
00:06:07.330 --> 00:06:08.910
<i>with the giant sandworms</i>

69
00:06:09.330 --> 00:06:11.530
<i>known to the Fremen as</i> Shai-Hulud.

70
00:06:12.620 --> 00:06:15.210
<i>Long exposure to spice
has given the tribe</i>

71
00:06:15.290 --> 00:06:17.250
<i>their characteristic blue eyes.</i>

72
00:06:18.210 --> 00:06:19.870
<i>the Eyes of Ibad.</i>

73
00:06:20.170 --> 00:06:21.960
<i>Little else is known of the Fremen.</i>

74
00:06:23.010 --> 00:06:25.880
<i>except that they are dangerous
and unreliable.</i>

75
00:06:27.680 --> 00:06:29.890
<i>Fremen attacks make spice harvesting</i>

76
00:06:29.970 --> 00:06:31.710
<i>extremely hazardous.</i>

77
00:06:32.600 --> 00:06:35.720
<i>For the Fremen.
spice is the sacred hallucinogen</i>

78
00:06:35.980 --> 00:06:37.060
<i>which preserves life</i>

79
00:06:37.150 --> 00:06:39.350
<i>and brings enormous health benefits.</i>

80
00:06:40.780 --> 00:06:41.690
<i>For the Imperium.</i>

81
00:06:41.780 --> 00:06:43.810
<i>spice is used by the navigators</i>

82
00:06:43.900 --> 00:06:45.610
<i>of the Spacing Guild</i>

83
00:06:45.700 --> 00:06:48.230
<i>to find safe paths between the stars.</i>

84
00:06:48.780 --> 00:06:49.820
<i>Without spice.</i>

85
00:06:50.040 --> 00:06:52.490
<i>interstellar travel is impossible.</i>

86
00:06:53.040 --> 00:06:54.150
<i>making it by far</i>

87
00:06:54.250 --> 00:06:57.160
<i>the most valuable substance
in the universe.</i>

88
00:06:57.880 --> 00:06:59.580
[SLOW DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

89
00:07:27.160 --> 00:07:28.740
[SLOW DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

90
00:07:47.050 --> 00:07:48.090
Smile. Gurney.

91
00:07:49.300 --> 00:07:50.510
I am smiling.

92
00:07:52.310 --> 00:07:53.640
How much will it cost them.

93
00:07:54.060 --> 00:07:56.050
traveling all this way
for this formality?

94
00:07:56.690 --> 00:07:57.680
Three Guild Navigators.

95
00:07:57.770 --> 00:08:01.510
A total of 1.46 million.
62 solaris. round trip.

96
00:08:17.620 --> 00:08:20.280
By the grace of Shaddam IV
of House Corrino.

97
00:08:20.830 --> 00:08:22.790
ascendant to the Golden Lion Throne

98
00:08:22.880 --> 00:08:25.240
of Padishah Emperor
of the Known Universe.

99
00:08:25.880 --> 00:08:29.000
I stand before you
as Herald of the Change.

100
00:08:30.140 --> 00:08:32.550
We are witnessed by members
of the Imperial Court.

101
00:08:33.180 --> 00:08:35.220
representatives of the Spacing Guild

102
00:08:35.770 --> 00:08:38.430
and a sister of the Bene Gesserit.

103
00:08:40.350 --> 00:08:42.560
The Emperor has spoken.

104
00:08:44.190 --> 00:08:48.400
"House Atreides shall immediately
take control of Arrakis

105
00:08:49.110 --> 00:08:51.600
and serve as its steward."

106
00:08:53.700 --> 00:08:54.690
Do you accept?

107
00:09:04.960 --> 00:09:06.370
[LETO] We are House Atreides.

108
00:09:07.880 --> 00:09:11.620
There is no call we do not answer.
there is no faith that we betray.

109
00:09:12.430 --> 00:09:16.010
The Emperor asks us
to bring peace to Arrakis.

110
00:09:17.310 --> 00:09:19.140
House Atreides accepts.

111
00:09:20.020 --> 00:09:23.680
[OFFICERS CHANTING]
Atreides! Atreides! Atreides!

112
00:09:24.230 --> 00:09:27.810
Atreides! Atreides! Atreides!

113
00:09:35.830 --> 00:09:36.860
Your seal.

114
00:10:13.280 --> 00:10:14.270
So. it's done?

115
00:10:16.160 --> 00:10:17.150
It's done.

116
00:10:43.810 --> 00:10:44.800
[LANVILLE] How was it?

117
00:10:45.560 --> 00:10:47.020
[DUNCAN OVER MASK]
Stabilizers are too loose.

118
00:10:47.440 --> 00:10:49.350
- We'll dial it in.
- Thank you. my friend.

119
00:10:49.440 --> 00:10:50.480
[LANVILLE] Got it.

120
00:10:51.280 --> 00:10:52.230
[PAUL] Duncan.

121
00:10:52.400 --> 00:10:53.390
[DUNCAN] My boy.

122
00:10:53.570 --> 00:10:54.780
- [DUNCAN CHUCKLES]
- Hey. Hey.

123
00:10:55.160 --> 00:10:56.270
[DUNCAN] Paul. my boy.

124
00:10:58.450 --> 00:10:59.860
So. you're going to Arrakis tomorrow.

125
00:11:00.910 --> 00:11:01.990
With the advance team.

126
00:11:02.500 --> 00:11:03.740
Yes. I'm going to Arrakis tomorrow

127
00:11:03.830 --> 00:11:04.870
with the advance team.

128
00:11:06.460 --> 00:11:07.660
I'd like you to take me with you.

129
00:11:08.750 --> 00:11:09.740
You would?

130
00:11:11.130 --> 00:11:12.540
Well. that's too bad. 'Cause no.

131
00:11:14.010 --> 00:11:15.040
[PAUL] Duncan.

132
00:11:15.220 --> 00:11:17.000
Are you trying
to get me court-martialed?

133
00:11:18.640 --> 00:11:19.720
What's going on?

134
00:11:19.800 --> 00:11:20.840
Can I trust you with something?

135
00:11:21.350 --> 00:11:22.300
Always. You know that.

136
00:11:24.390 --> 00:11:25.470
[SIGHS]

137
00:11:29.230 --> 00:11:30.890
I've been having dreams.

138
00:11:33.320 --> 00:11:35.430
About Arrakis and the Fremen.

139
00:11:35.950 --> 00:11:37.940
[ETHEREAL MUSIC PLAYING]

140
00:11:44.290 --> 00:11:45.370
[DUNCAN] Okay.

141
00:11:46.080 --> 00:11:47.200
So?

142
00:11:48.750 --> 00:11:49.830
I saw you.

143
00:11:53.340 --> 00:11:54.500
<i>With the Fremen.</i>

144
00:11:55.420 --> 00:11:56.410
Ah.

145
00:11:57.340 --> 00:11:58.500
So. I do find them.

146
00:11:58.720 --> 00:12:00.710
There you go. That's a good
omen right there. right?

147
00:12:03.470 --> 00:12:04.460
Lanville!

148
00:12:11.190 --> 00:12:12.650
I saw you lying dead.

149
00:12:13.570 --> 00:12:15.150
Fallen in battle.

150
00:12:17.150 --> 00:12:18.690
<i>It felt like if I had been there.</i>

151
00:12:19.450 --> 00:12:20.690
<i>you'd be alive.</i>

152
00:12:25.870 --> 00:12:27.580
First off. I'm not gonna die.

153
00:12:27.910 --> 00:12:29.000
You're not taking me seriously.

154
00:12:29.080 --> 00:12:30.870
That's why you want
to come with me. Listen.

155
00:12:32.790 --> 00:12:34.030
Dreams make good stories.

156
00:12:34.590 --> 00:12:36.500
but everything important
happens when we're awake.

157
00:12:37.010 --> 00:12:38.370
'Cause that's when
we make things happen.

158
00:12:39.090 --> 00:12:41.080
Look at you. Put on some muscle?

159
00:12:41.390 --> 00:12:42.250
I did?

160
00:12:42.550 --> 00:12:43.630
No.

161
00:12:46.220 --> 00:12:47.390
Hey.

162
00:12:48.310 --> 00:12:49.890
See you on Arrakis. my boy.

163
00:12:52.860 --> 00:12:53.850
[SIGHS]

164
00:12:57.650 --> 00:12:58.810
[ANIMAL CHIRPING]

165
00:13:25.600 --> 00:13:27.550
Father. I'd like to ask
to join Duncan Idaho

166
00:13:27.640 --> 00:13:29.850
on his scout mission
to Arrakis tomorrow.

167
00:13:30.480 --> 00:13:32.140
I've studied the Fremen language.
I'd be an asset.

168
00:13:32.310 --> 00:13:33.430
Out of the question.

169
00:13:33.600 --> 00:13:34.970
You'll travel in a few weeks to Arrakis.

170
00:13:35.060 --> 00:13:36.050
like the rest of us.

171
00:13:36.230 --> 00:13:37.560
I've been training my whole life.

172
00:13:37.650 --> 00:13:39.140
What is the point if I'm not allowed

173
00:13:39.240 --> 00:13:41.020
- to face some actual risk?
- You know why. Paul.

174
00:13:41.950 --> 00:13:43.780
You're the future of House Atreides.

175
00:13:44.120 --> 00:13:46.110
And Grandfather fought bulls for sport!

176
00:13:46.200 --> 00:13:47.070
Yes.

177
00:13:48.330 --> 00:13:49.490
And look where that got him.

178
00:13:54.250 --> 00:13:55.620
I need you by my side.

179
00:13:56.880 --> 00:13:59.210
When we get to Arrakis.
we'll face enormous danger.

180
00:13:59.630 --> 00:14:00.710
What danger?

181
00:14:01.420 --> 00:14:03.260
The Fremen? The desert?

182
00:14:03.340 --> 00:14:04.800
Political danger.

183
00:14:07.430 --> 00:14:09.890
The Great Houses
look to us for leadership.

184
00:14:10.520 --> 00:14:12.180
and this threatens the Emperor.

185
00:14:12.810 --> 00:14:15.720
By taking Arrakis from the Harkonnens
and making it ours.

186
00:14:16.110 --> 00:14:17.600
he sets the stage for a war

187
00:14:18.230 --> 00:14:19.890
which would weaken both houses.

188
00:14:21.860 --> 00:14:23.230
But if we hold firm.

189
00:14:23.820 --> 00:14:25.730
and tap the true power of Arrakis.

190
00:14:25.820 --> 00:14:27.610
we could be stronger than ever.

191
00:14:28.120 --> 00:14:29.200
What does that mean?

192
00:14:30.040 --> 00:14:32.490
Mining spice.
keeping the Fremen in their place?

193
00:14:32.660 --> 00:14:34.320
- We'd be no better than Harkonnens.
- No.

194
00:14:35.670 --> 00:14:38.030
By making an alliance with the Fremen.

195
00:14:38.960 --> 00:14:41.080
That's what I've sent
Duncan Idaho to arrange.

196
00:14:42.760 --> 00:14:43.670
Here on Caladan.

197
00:14:43.800 --> 00:14:46.540
we've ruled by air power and sea power.

198
00:14:46.800 --> 00:14:50.140
On Arrakis. we need
to cultivate desert power.

199
00:14:53.940 --> 00:14:55.350
I want you sitting in on my Council.

200
00:14:55.650 --> 00:14:56.730
Learn what I do.

201
00:14:57.190 --> 00:14:58.390
What if I'm not. Dad?

202
00:14:59.860 --> 00:15:00.720
Not what?

203
00:15:03.400 --> 00:15:05.140
The future of House Atreides.

204
00:15:08.450 --> 00:15:09.480
[LETO SIGHS]

205
00:15:18.210 --> 00:15:20.120
I told my father
I didn't want this either.

206
00:15:24.630 --> 00:15:25.790
I wanted to be a pilot.

207
00:15:27.800 --> 00:15:28.960
You never told me that.

208
00:15:32.310 --> 00:15:33.510
Your grandfather said.

209
00:15:34.560 --> 00:15:36.550
"A great man doesn't seek to lead.

210
00:15:37.350 --> 00:15:40.390
He's called to it. and he answers."

211
00:15:42.650 --> 00:15:44.190
And if your answer is no...

212
00:15:47.780 --> 00:15:50.070
you'll still be the only thing
I ever needed you to be...

213
00:15:52.580 --> 00:15:53.610
my son.

214
00:16:04.130 --> 00:16:07.670
I found my own way to it.
Maybe you'll find yours.

215
00:16:11.470 --> 00:16:12.710
In their memory...

216
00:16:15.890 --> 00:16:16.970
give it a try.

217
00:16:24.400 --> 00:16:25.730
[GRUNTING]

218
00:16:26.440 --> 00:16:28.440
[GURNEY] Don't stand
with your back to the door.

219
00:16:29.950 --> 00:16:31.480
How many times do we have to tell you?

220
00:16:31.570 --> 00:16:32.990
[PAUL GRUNTS] I could tell it was you

221
00:16:33.080 --> 00:16:34.740
by your footsteps. Gurney Halleck.

222
00:16:34.910 --> 00:16:36.990
[GURNEY] Someone
might imitate my stride.

223
00:16:37.710 --> 00:16:38.990
[PAUL] I know the difference.

224
00:16:39.170 --> 00:16:40.660
Are you the new Weapons Master?

225
00:16:40.830 --> 00:16:44.330
With Duncan Idaho gone.
I must make do as best I can.

226
00:16:45.550 --> 00:16:46.540
Choose your blade.

227
00:16:47.010 --> 00:16:48.290
I've had quite a day. Gurney.

228
00:16:48.970 --> 00:16:50.130
Give us a song instead.

229
00:16:55.430 --> 00:16:56.470
[SMACKS LIPS] That's rude.

230
00:16:57.850 --> 00:16:59.010
[PAUL GRUNTS]

231
00:17:01.400 --> 00:17:02.310
[POWERS UP]

232
00:17:06.610 --> 00:17:07.520
[DEVICE BEEPS]

233
00:17:11.320 --> 00:17:12.280
[PAUL GROANS]

234
00:17:12.490 --> 00:17:13.480
[PANTING]

235
00:17:14.030 --> 00:17:14.990
[GURNEY] Come on.

236
00:17:15.620 --> 00:17:16.610
Come on.

237
00:17:16.700 --> 00:17:17.690
Old man.

238
00:17:18.080 --> 00:17:19.070
[EXHALES FORCEFULLY]

239
00:17:25.290 --> 00:17:26.280
[PAUL GRUNTS]

240
00:17:27.840 --> 00:17:29.290
[DEVICE BEEPS]

241
00:17:29.760 --> 00:17:31.960
Ah. the slow blade
penetrates the shield.

242
00:17:36.970 --> 00:17:37.930
[GROANS]

243
00:17:39.390 --> 00:17:40.510
I guess I'm not in the mood today.

244
00:17:41.230 --> 00:17:42.340
- Mood?
- Yeah.

245
00:17:42.520 --> 00:17:43.510
What's mood to do with it?

246
00:17:43.690 --> 00:17:45.430
You fight when the necessity arises.

247
00:17:45.520 --> 00:17:46.510
no matter the mood.

248
00:17:46.610 --> 00:17:47.640
Now fight!

249
00:17:49.360 --> 00:17:50.940
[BOTH GRUNTING]

250
00:17:53.160 --> 00:17:54.150
Come on!

251
00:18:05.960 --> 00:18:07.830
- [DEVICE BEEPS]
- I have you.

252
00:18:08.300 --> 00:18:09.410
Aye.

253
00:18:10.170 --> 00:18:11.750
But look down. my lord.

254
00:18:11.920 --> 00:18:13.590
You'd have joined me in death.

255
00:18:14.590 --> 00:18:16.380
I see you found the mood.

256
00:18:17.680 --> 00:18:18.970
[GURNEY PANTING]

257
00:18:23.520 --> 00:18:26.390
[DEVICES DEACTIVATE]

258
00:18:28.860 --> 00:18:29.940
Will it be that bad?

259
00:18:30.480 --> 00:18:31.650
You don't get it. do you?

260
00:18:33.110 --> 00:18:34.230
You don't really understand

261
00:18:34.320 --> 00:18:36.690
the grave nature
of what's happening to us.

262
00:18:39.540 --> 00:18:40.900
For 80 years.

263
00:18:41.000 --> 00:18:43.080
Arrakis belonged to House Harkonnen.

264
00:18:43.250 --> 00:18:45.580
80 years of owning the spice fields.

265
00:18:45.920 --> 00:18:47.500
Can you imagine the wealth?

266
00:18:48.040 --> 00:18:49.880
Your eyes.
I need to see it in your eyes.

267
00:18:50.050 --> 00:18:52.330
You never met Harkonnens
before. I have.

268
00:18:52.800 --> 00:18:54.660
They're not human. they're brutal!

269
00:18:55.680 --> 00:18:57.210
You have to be ready.

270
00:19:07.940 --> 00:19:09.720
[DRAMATIC OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

271
00:19:39.550 --> 00:19:40.590
[RABBAN] Lord Baron.

272
00:19:42.930 --> 00:19:44.010
[VLADIMIR] Rabban.

273
00:19:45.230 --> 00:19:47.180
The last of our ships have left Arrakis.

274
00:19:48.690 --> 00:19:49.680
It's done.

275
00:19:50.360 --> 00:19:51.440
[VLADIMIR] Very good.

276
00:19:54.990 --> 00:19:56.320
Uncle. how can we let this happen?

277
00:19:57.030 --> 00:19:57.940
How can the Emperor...

278
00:19:59.370 --> 00:20:01.400
[SHOUTING] ...take everything
we've built

279
00:20:01.990 --> 00:20:03.400
and give it to that Duke?

280
00:20:04.080 --> 00:20:05.070
How?

281
00:20:05.710 --> 00:20:07.570
Don't be too sure it's an act of love.

282
00:20:08.290 --> 00:20:09.530
[BREATHES HEAVILY]

283
00:20:10.460 --> 00:20:11.370
What does he mean?

284
00:20:17.970 --> 00:20:20.210
When is a gift not a gift?

285
00:20:22.600 --> 00:20:25.090
The Atreides' voice is rising.

286
00:20:26.430 --> 00:20:28.770
and the Emperor is a jealous man.

287
00:20:31.810 --> 00:20:34.600
A dangerous. jealous man.

288
00:20:35.900 --> 00:20:37.270
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

289
00:20:49.330 --> 00:20:51.120
[VOICES CHANTING INDISTINCTLY]

290
00:21:02.600 --> 00:21:04.090
[VOICES CONTINUE CHANTING]

291
00:21:32.960 --> 00:21:33.820
[VOICES FADE]

292
00:21:45.930 --> 00:21:46.800
Paul.

293
00:21:48.720 --> 00:21:49.840
[SOFTLY] Paul. wake up.

294
00:21:56.440 --> 00:21:57.430
What's wrong?

295
00:21:57.530 --> 00:21:58.860
Get dressed and come with me.

296
00:22:20.170 --> 00:22:21.330
What is this?

297
00:22:21.510 --> 00:22:23.870
The Reverend Mother
Gaius Helen Mohiam is here.

298
00:22:24.800 --> 00:22:26.840
She was my teacher
at the Bene Gesserit school.

299
00:22:27.010 --> 00:22:29.380
She's now Truthsayer
to the Emperor himself.

300
00:22:30.520 --> 00:22:31.970
She would like to meet you.

301
00:22:32.890 --> 00:22:33.970
Why?

302
00:22:34.940 --> 00:22:36.550
She wants to know about your dreams.

303
00:22:38.440 --> 00:22:40.100
How does she know about my dreams?

304
00:22:42.900 --> 00:22:44.360
And why is Dr. Yueh here?

305
00:22:44.530 --> 00:22:45.900
He only needs a moment.

306
00:22:47.030 --> 00:22:48.270
[DR. YUEH] Hello. young master.

307
00:22:49.200 --> 00:22:51.160
Your mother asked me
to check your vitals.

308
00:22:57.710 --> 00:22:58.750
What's happening?

309
00:23:02.010 --> 00:23:02.960
[WHISPERING IN MANDARIN]

310
00:23:20.690 --> 00:23:22.730
[IN ENGLISH] His heart
is strong as ever. my lady.

311
00:23:24.240 --> 00:23:25.230
[IN SIGN LANGUAGE]

312
00:23:37.500 --> 00:23:38.610
Paul...

313
00:23:42.090 --> 00:23:43.080
[IN SIGN LANGUAGE]

314
00:24:06.400 --> 00:24:11.770
[EERIE VOICES] Who are <i>you?</i>

315
00:24:16.250 --> 00:24:17.910
Defiance in the eyes.

316
00:24:18.710 --> 00:24:19.820
Like his father.

317
00:24:20.250 --> 00:24:21.240
Leave us.

318
00:24:22.210 --> 00:24:24.250
[WHISPERS] You must do everything
the Reverend Mother tells you.

319
00:24:28.180 --> 00:24:29.510
You dismiss my mother
in her own house.

320
00:24:29.590 --> 00:24:30.670
[MOHIAM IN DISTORTED VOICE] Come here.

321
00:24:31.260 --> 00:24:32.250
Kneel.

322
00:24:36.730 --> 00:24:38.310
How dare you use the Voice on me?

323
00:24:45.860 --> 00:24:47.020
[NORMAL VOICE] Put your right
hand in the box.

324
00:24:49.320 --> 00:24:51.150
Your mother bade you obey me.

325
00:24:52.030 --> 00:24:53.070
[PAUL BREATHES HEAVILY]

326
00:25:00.420 --> 00:25:02.080
I hold at your neck the Gom Jabbar.

327
00:25:03.590 --> 00:25:04.620
A poison needle.

328
00:25:05.090 --> 00:25:06.120
Instant death.

329
00:25:07.550 --> 00:25:08.580
The test is simple.

330
00:25:09.130 --> 00:25:10.670
Remove your hand from the box

331
00:25:11.550 --> 00:25:12.540
and you die.

332
00:25:14.350 --> 00:25:15.460
What's in the box?

333
00:25:17.220 --> 00:25:18.090
Pain.

334
00:25:19.850 --> 00:25:21.930
- [SCOFFS]
- No need to call the guards.

335
00:25:23.270 --> 00:25:24.680
Your mother stands behind that door.

336
00:25:24.770 --> 00:25:26.360
No one would get past her.

337
00:25:33.660 --> 00:25:34.860
[PAUL] Why are you doing this?

338
00:25:36.700 --> 00:25:40.820
An animal caught in a trap
will gnaw off its own leg to escape.

339
00:25:41.580 --> 00:25:42.820
What will you do?

340
00:25:48.710 --> 00:25:50.330
[HIGH-PITCHED WHIRRING]

341
00:25:55.350 --> 00:25:56.510
[GROANS]

342
00:26:00.430 --> 00:26:01.550
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

343
00:26:05.610 --> 00:26:06.890
[SOBBING SOFTLY]

344
00:26:08.480 --> 00:26:09.770
[SHUDDERS]

345
00:26:14.820 --> 00:26:16.310
- [GRUNTS IN PAIN]
- Silence.

346
00:26:17.030 --> 00:26:18.650
[PAUL BREATHING RAGGEDLY]

347
00:26:24.000 --> 00:26:25.660
- [PAUL GRUNTS IN PAIN]
- [SHUDDERING]

348
00:26:26.130 --> 00:26:27.540
I must not fear.

349
00:26:29.550 --> 00:26:30.880
I must not fear.

350
00:26:32.260 --> 00:26:34.370
[STIFLES GRUNT. WHIMPERS]

351
00:26:34.720 --> 00:26:36.710
[SUPPRESSED GROAN]

352
00:26:37.640 --> 00:26:39.000
Fear is the mind-killer.

353
00:26:41.270 --> 00:26:42.350
Fear

354
00:26:42.640 --> 00:26:44.880
is the little death
that brings obliteration.

355
00:26:45.230 --> 00:26:46.850
- [WHIRRING INTENSIFIES]
- [PAUL GRUNTS]

356
00:26:47.940 --> 00:26:49.650
And I'll face my fear and I'll permit it

357
00:26:49.730 --> 00:26:50.940
to pass over me and through me.

358
00:26:58.030 --> 00:26:59.740
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

359
00:27:01.290 --> 00:27:03.240
[DRAMATIC LAMENTATION MUSIC PLAYING]

360
00:27:04.160 --> 00:27:05.620
[SEARING]

361
00:27:06.290 --> 00:27:07.660
And when it has gone past...

362
00:27:16.550 --> 00:27:19.010
I will turn the inner eye
and see its path. [GASPS]

363
00:27:22.180 --> 00:27:24.770
[SOBS] And where the fear has gone.

364
00:27:25.890 --> 00:27:26.880
there will be nothing.

365
00:27:31.820 --> 00:27:33.150
Only I will remain.

366
00:27:37.660 --> 00:27:38.610
Enough.

367
00:27:38.910 --> 00:27:40.690
- [PANTING]
- [WHIRRING FADING]

368
00:27:55.670 --> 00:27:57.460
Like sifting sand through a screen.

369
00:27:58.300 --> 00:27:59.540
we sift people.

370
00:28:01.140 --> 00:28:03.600
If you had been unable
to control your impulses.

371
00:28:03.680 --> 00:28:04.840
like an animal.

372
00:28:05.730 --> 00:28:06.810
we could not let you live.

373
00:28:08.020 --> 00:28:09.430
You inherit too much power.

374
00:28:10.810 --> 00:28:11.800
What. because I'm a duke's son?

375
00:28:11.900 --> 00:28:13.480
Because you are Jessica's son.

376
00:28:15.070 --> 00:28:17.060
You have more than one birthright. boy.

377
00:28:19.030 --> 00:28:20.020
Jessica?

378
00:28:27.370 --> 00:28:28.910
You've been training him in the Way.

379
00:28:33.840 --> 00:28:35.450
Tell me about these dreams.

380
00:28:36.760 --> 00:28:38.750
- I had one tonight.
- What did you see?

381
00:28:41.350 --> 00:28:42.340
A girl.

382
00:28:43.140 --> 00:28:44.130
On Arrakis.

383
00:28:44.930 --> 00:28:46.260
Have you dreamt of her before?

384
00:28:50.600 --> 00:28:51.720
Many times.

385
00:28:54.480 --> 00:28:56.440
Do you often dream things that happen

386
00:28:56.530 --> 00:28:57.730
just as you dreamed them?

387
00:29:01.240 --> 00:29:02.320
Not exactly.

388
00:29:06.040 --> 00:29:07.280
Goodbye. young human.

389
00:29:08.410 --> 00:29:09.570
I hope you live.

390
00:29:18.260 --> 00:29:20.000
[LADY JESSICA]
Did you have to go that far?

391
00:29:20.380 --> 00:29:21.670
[MOHIAM] You chose
to train him in the Way.

392
00:29:22.140 --> 00:29:23.470
in defiance of our rule.

393
00:29:24.050 --> 00:29:25.470
He wields our power.

394
00:29:25.720 --> 00:29:27.340
He had to be tested to the limits.

395
00:29:28.680 --> 00:29:30.720
So much potential. wasted in a male.

396
00:29:32.020 --> 00:29:33.640
You were told to bear only daughters.

397
00:29:33.940 --> 00:29:34.970
But you. in your pride.

398
00:29:35.070 --> 00:29:37.060
thought you could
produce the <i>Kwisatz Haderach.</i>

399
00:29:37.440 --> 00:29:38.560
Was I wrong?

400
00:29:39.030 --> 00:29:40.770
You're lucky he didn't die in that room.

401
00:29:41.910 --> 00:29:43.940
If he is The One.
he has a long way to go.

402
00:29:44.240 --> 00:29:46.900
His Sight is barely awakened.
and now he goes into the fire.

403
00:29:48.500 --> 00:29:50.700
But our plans are measured in centuries.

404
00:29:50.870 --> 00:29:52.160
We have other prospects

405
00:29:52.750 --> 00:29:54.460
if he fails his promise.

406
00:29:57.590 --> 00:29:59.000
Do you see so little hope?

407
00:30:00.130 --> 00:30:02.750
[MOHIAM] On Arrakis. we have done
all we can for you.

408
00:30:03.340 --> 00:30:04.670
A path has been laid.

409
00:30:05.350 --> 00:30:07.090
Let's hope he doesn't squander it.

410
00:30:14.440 --> 00:30:16.100
[VOICES MURMURING INDISTINCTLY]

411
00:30:49.100 --> 00:30:50.380
[BREATHES HEAVILY]

412
00:30:54.640 --> 00:30:55.600
[LADY JESSICA] Paul.

413
00:30:57.150 --> 00:30:58.350
[PAUL] What does it mean?

414
00:31:00.030 --> 00:31:01.270
That I could be The One?

415
00:31:01.650 --> 00:31:02.810
[LADY JESSICA] You heard.

416
00:31:06.370 --> 00:31:07.610
The Bene Gesserit serve

417
00:31:07.700 --> 00:31:09.690
as powerful partners
to the Great Houses.

418
00:31:11.160 --> 00:31:12.280
but there's more to it.

419
00:31:12.750 --> 00:31:14.990
You steer the politics of the Imperium

420
00:31:15.080 --> 00:31:16.450
from the shadows.

421
00:31:17.250 --> 00:31:18.240
I know.

422
00:31:18.340 --> 00:31:20.000
You don't know everything.

423
00:31:21.510 --> 00:31:23.210
For thousands of years.

424
00:31:23.380 --> 00:31:25.540
we've been carefully crossing bloodlines

425
00:31:26.130 --> 00:31:27.840
- to bring forth--
- The One?

426
00:31:29.430 --> 00:31:30.640
A mind...

427
00:31:32.810 --> 00:31:36.720
powerful enough
to bridge space and time.

428
00:31:37.730 --> 00:31:39.220
Past and future.

429
00:31:41.730 --> 00:31:43.940
Who can help us into a better future.

430
00:31:45.200 --> 00:31:47.360
We think he's very close now.

431
00:31:49.780 --> 00:31:51.490
Some believe he's here.

432
00:31:55.960 --> 00:31:57.620
All part of a plan.

433
00:32:14.980 --> 00:32:16.560
[SLOW DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

434
00:32:52.100 --> 00:32:53.590
[SLOW DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

435
00:34:12.630 --> 00:34:14.090
[SPACESHIP LANDS]

436
00:34:15.930 --> 00:34:16.890
Shield.

437
00:34:27.940 --> 00:34:29.430
[METALLIC GROAN]

438
00:34:32.360 --> 00:34:33.600
[METALLIC THUDDING]

439
00:34:34.700 --> 00:34:35.780
[DOOR OPENS]

440
00:34:59.680 --> 00:35:01.510
"My lungs taste the air of Time.

441
00:35:01.600 --> 00:35:03.180
Blown past falling sand..."

442
00:35:03.640 --> 00:35:04.850
[BAGPIPE PLAYING]

443
00:35:15.360 --> 00:35:17.350
[BAND PLAYING PATRIOTIC MUSIC]

444
00:35:48.230 --> 00:35:49.190
Thufir Hawat.

445
00:35:53.860 --> 00:35:55.350
Young master!

446
00:35:55.530 --> 00:35:57.640
How does it feel
to walk on a new world?

447
00:35:57.820 --> 00:35:59.650
Exciting. to say the least.

448
00:36:00.370 --> 00:36:01.530
My lord.

449
00:36:02.370 --> 00:36:03.360
How are you. old friend?

450
00:36:04.290 --> 00:36:06.400
My advance team has secured the city.

451
00:36:06.750 --> 00:36:08.790
We're still smoothing out
a few rough spots.

452
00:36:11.040 --> 00:36:12.130
My lady.

453
00:36:16.930 --> 00:36:18.380
[WOMAN] <i>Lisan al-Gaib!</i>

454
00:36:30.980 --> 00:36:32.560
[CROWD CLAMORING]

455
00:36:34.730 --> 00:36:37.440
[MAN] <i>Lisan al-Gaib! Lisan al-Gaib!</i>

456
00:36:38.740 --> 00:36:39.820
[WOMAN 2] <i>Lisan al-Gaib!</i>

457
00:36:39.950 --> 00:36:42.660
[CROWD CHANTING]
<i>Lisan al-Gaib! Lisan al-Gaib!</i>

458
00:36:43.330 --> 00:36:45.660
<i>Lisan al-Gaib! Lisan al-Gaib!</i>

459
00:36:46.410 --> 00:36:48.650
<i>Lisan al-Gaib! Lisan al-Gaib!</i>

460
00:36:49.370 --> 00:36:51.960
<i>Lisan al-Gaib! Lisan al-Gaib!</i>

461
00:36:53.960 --> 00:36:55.670
Don't be fooled by the welcome.

462
00:36:55.960 --> 00:36:57.630
They follow their old masters' rules.

463
00:36:57.720 --> 00:36:58.710
Mandatory attendance.

464
00:36:58.880 --> 00:37:00.670
That's Harkonnen love out there.

465
00:37:02.220 --> 00:37:03.510
[CROWD CONTINUES CHANTING]

466
00:37:07.680 --> 00:37:08.670
Atreides!

467
00:37:08.850 --> 00:37:12.640
[SOLDIERS CHANTING]
Atreides! Atreides! Atreides!

468
00:37:12.980 --> 00:37:16.690
Atreides! Atreides! Atreides!

469
00:37:17.070 --> 00:37:19.060
Atreides! Atreides!

470
00:37:21.700 --> 00:37:23.190
[THUFIR] Let's get you out of the sun.

471
00:37:24.280 --> 00:37:26.150
The heat can kill in this place.

472
00:37:35.960 --> 00:37:37.790
[ORNITHOPTERS POWERING UP]

473
00:37:43.140 --> 00:37:44.300
They were pointing at us.

474
00:37:45.720 --> 00:37:46.710
What are they shouting?

475
00:37:47.140 --> 00:37:50.850
<i>Lisan al-Gaib.</i>
"Voice from the Outer World."

476
00:37:51.140 --> 00:37:52.560
It's their name for "messiah."

477
00:37:54.150 --> 00:37:56.480
It means the Bene Gesserit
have been at work here.

478
00:37:57.480 --> 00:37:59.150
Planting superstitions.

479
00:37:59.860 --> 00:38:01.820
Preparing the way. Paul.

480
00:38:02.820 --> 00:38:05.060
These people
have waited for centuries

481
00:38:05.160 --> 00:38:06.440
for the <i>Lisan al-Gaib.</i>

482
00:38:07.580 --> 00:38:08.610
They see you.

483
00:38:09.540 --> 00:38:10.950
they see the signs.

484
00:38:14.210 --> 00:38:16.040
They see what they've been
told to see.

485
00:38:21.550 --> 00:38:22.540
We're good to go.

486
00:39:06.180 --> 00:39:07.170
[THUFIR] Shield Wall.

487
00:39:07.470 --> 00:39:10.510
Protects the city from the weather
and the worms.

488
00:39:19.650 --> 00:39:21.610
[EERIE DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

489
00:39:57.850 --> 00:40:00.390
[GURNEY] The locals call
the big one the Hand of God.

490
00:40:02.570 --> 00:40:04.930
[LETO] Well. the Hand of God
is wreaking havoc

491
00:40:05.030 --> 00:40:06.230
on our comms system.

492
00:40:09.950 --> 00:40:11.060
It's so quiet.

493
00:40:12.410 --> 00:40:13.400
[GURNEY] Yeah.

494
00:40:14.450 --> 00:40:15.870
That's what worries me. too.

495
00:40:23.090 --> 00:40:24.290
[LETO] There's the spaceport

496
00:40:25.050 --> 00:40:27.510
and that plume of dust there
is the spice refinery.

497
00:40:27.880 --> 00:40:29.370
Our two most vulnerable points.

498
00:40:29.760 --> 00:40:31.000
I want you guarding them.

499
00:40:31.350 --> 00:40:33.760
If we can't refine spice
and ship it off-world.

500
00:40:33.930 --> 00:40:35.300
- we're dead here.
- [LANVILLE] My lord.

501
00:40:36.430 --> 00:40:38.680
The sun's getting too high.
We need to seal the doors.

502
00:40:41.560 --> 00:40:42.550
[LETO SIGHS]

503
00:40:42.820 --> 00:40:44.680
What do they say
about this hellhole again?

504
00:40:46.070 --> 00:40:48.150
"To shower. you scrub your ass
with sand." my lord.

505
00:40:48.280 --> 00:40:49.570
That's what they say.

506
00:40:49.860 --> 00:40:51.070
That's what they say.

507
00:40:56.200 --> 00:40:57.910
[THUFIR] Candidates
for a housekeeper. my lady.

508
00:41:14.760 --> 00:41:15.720
What is your name?

509
00:41:16.350 --> 00:41:17.710
Shadout Mapes. my lady.

510
00:41:20.230 --> 00:41:21.590
[LADY JESSICA] The rest of you may go.

511
00:41:22.060 --> 00:41:23.100
Thank you.

512
00:41:25.650 --> 00:41:26.610
Shadout.

513
00:41:27.740 --> 00:41:29.070
It's an old Chakobsa word.

514
00:41:30.200 --> 00:41:31.280
"Well-dipper."

515
00:41:32.030 --> 00:41:33.020
[SPEAKING CHAKOBSA]

516
00:41:34.280 --> 00:41:35.610
[IN ENGLISH]
You know the ancient tongues?

517
00:41:35.790 --> 00:41:36.900
I know many things.

518
00:41:37.500 --> 00:41:40.240
I know that you have a weapon
concealed in your bodice.

519
00:41:40.420 --> 00:41:41.500
[IN SIGN LANGUAGE]

520
00:41:42.540 --> 00:41:43.700
[SPEAKING] If you mean to harm me.

521
00:41:44.790 --> 00:41:46.750
I must warn you.
whatever you're hiding.

522
00:41:47.840 --> 00:41:49.130
it won't be enough.

523
00:41:51.380 --> 00:41:53.300
The weapon is meant as a gift

524
00:41:54.760 --> 00:41:56.420
if you are truly The One.

525
00:42:12.570 --> 00:42:13.900
Do you know this?

526
00:42:15.740 --> 00:42:17.110
It's a crysknife.

527
00:42:21.000 --> 00:42:22.160
Do you know its meaning?

528
00:42:22.250 --> 00:42:23.240
[IN SIGN LANGUAGE]

529
00:42:26.590 --> 00:42:27.830
It's a maker...

530
00:42:28.170 --> 00:42:29.790
[WAILING]

531
00:42:33.510 --> 00:42:35.420
A maker of the deep desert.

532
00:42:38.680 --> 00:42:40.720
When you have lived
with prophecy for so long.

533
00:42:40.890 --> 00:42:42.970
the moment of revelation
is a shock.

534
00:42:43.810 --> 00:42:44.970
<i>Lisan al-Gaib.</i>

535
00:42:45.440 --> 00:42:46.640
The mother and the son.

536
00:42:53.490 --> 00:42:54.690
It is yours.

537
00:42:56.820 --> 00:43:00.030
Tooth of <i>Shai-Hulud.</i>

538
00:43:02.370 --> 00:43:03.530
[ANCIENT MEDITATION MUSIC PLAYING]

539
00:43:30.530 --> 00:43:32.480
[MEN CHANTING IN DISTANCE]
<i>Lisan! Lisan al-Gaib!</i>

540
00:43:33.690 --> 00:43:37.310
<i>Lisan al-Gaib! Lisan al-Gaib!</i>

541
00:43:47.670 --> 00:43:48.580
[PAUL] Hello.

542
00:43:51.550 --> 00:43:53.500
You shouldn't be out here
at this hour of the day.

543
00:43:56.130 --> 00:43:57.220
They're out here.

544
00:43:58.430 --> 00:44:00.460
[GARDENER] Hmm. Fremen pilgrims.

545
00:44:01.470 --> 00:44:03.130
They don't care about heatstroke.

546
00:44:05.230 --> 00:44:07.260
I didn't know date palms
could even be found out here.

547
00:44:08.350 --> 00:44:10.850
[GARDENER] Oh. these aren't indigenous.

548
00:44:11.650 --> 00:44:13.190
They can't survive without me.

549
00:44:14.110 --> 00:44:15.100
Each one of these

550
00:44:15.190 --> 00:44:17.530
drinks every day
the equivalent of five men.

551
00:44:20.160 --> 00:44:21.520
Twenty palm trees.

552
00:44:22.990 --> 00:44:24.110
A hundred lives.

553
00:44:25.750 --> 00:44:27.860
Should we remove them?
Save the water?

554
00:44:27.960 --> 00:44:28.990
No. no. no.

555
00:44:29.250 --> 00:44:30.460
These are sacred.

556
00:44:35.260 --> 00:44:36.500
Old dream.

557
00:44:44.850 --> 00:44:46.840
[NARRATOR OVER SPEAKERS]
The largest and most dangerous

558
00:44:46.930 --> 00:44:49.800
<i>organism on Arrakis is the sandworm.</i>

559
00:44:50.230 --> 00:44:53.640
<i>capable of reaching
400 meters in length.</i>

560
00:44:54.280 --> 00:44:57.440
<i>To avoid making rhythmic noises.
which attract the sandworms.</i>

561
00:44:58.240 --> 00:45:02.320
<i>the Fremen cross desert spaces
using the sandwalk.</i>

562
00:45:02.450 --> 00:45:05.110
<i>a dance-like motion
with irregular rhythm</i>

563
00:45:05.240 --> 00:45:08.110
<i>which emulates the natural
sounds of the desert.</i>

564
00:45:09.500 --> 00:45:12.040
<i>What scant plant life
exists on Arrakis</i>

565
00:45:12.210 --> 00:45:13.790
<i>is thanks to the Fremen.</i>

566
00:45:13.880 --> 00:45:16.790
<i>who have cultivated
deep-rooted terranic plants</i>

567
00:45:17.090 --> 00:45:19.750
<i>such as saguaro. burrobush.</i>

568
00:45:20.130 --> 00:45:23.420
<i>sand-verbena and incense bush.</i>

569
00:45:24.430 --> 00:45:27.550
<i>The shepherd's tree has
the deepest documented roots.</i>

570
00:45:27.730 --> 00:45:30.430
<i>stretching more than 450 feet deep.</i>

571
00:45:30.520 --> 00:45:31.680
[SEARING]

572
00:45:32.150 --> 00:45:33.980
<i>These plants cling to life</i>

573
00:45:34.230 --> 00:45:36.890
<i>in a parched. nutrient-poor landscape.</i>

574
00:45:50.960 --> 00:45:52.790
[SLOW SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

575
00:46:33.500 --> 00:46:35.740
[MUSIC BUILDING UP]

576
00:46:42.050 --> 00:46:43.340
[BOTH GASP]

577
00:46:47.600 --> 00:46:48.960
[PAUL] It's a hunter-seeker.

578
00:46:49.430 --> 00:46:50.920
The operator must be nearby.

579
00:46:51.520 --> 00:46:53.050
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

580
00:46:56.610 --> 00:46:57.970
[THUFIR] <i>The Harkonnen agent
was cemented</i>

581
00:46:58.070 --> 00:46:59.400
<i>into that hole six weeks ago.</i>

582
00:47:00.110 --> 00:47:01.690
<i>Ran the hunter-seeker
through a water pipe</i>

583
00:47:01.780 --> 00:47:02.690
<i>inside the walls.</i>

584
00:47:04.240 --> 00:47:06.350
Sire. I failed you today.
There's no excuse.

585
00:47:07.280 --> 00:47:08.270
You have my resignation.

586
00:47:08.450 --> 00:47:09.990
You would deprive us
of your talents at this time?

587
00:47:10.370 --> 00:47:11.450
Sire. my honor demands--

588
00:47:11.540 --> 00:47:13.120
They tried to take the life of my son!

589
00:47:14.420 --> 00:47:15.870
I don't give a damn about your honor.

590
00:47:16.040 --> 00:47:18.250
You want absolution?
Go catch some spies.

591
00:47:18.710 --> 00:47:19.700
Your Grace.

592
00:47:27.260 --> 00:47:28.630
[MOHIAM] The thing must leave.

593
00:47:29.510 --> 00:47:31.050
[MAN] You can speak without fear.

594
00:47:32.100 --> 00:47:34.260
Our pet doesn't understand
your language.

595
00:47:34.440 --> 00:47:35.770
[MOHIAM IN DISTORTED VOICE] Get out.

596
00:47:40.320 --> 00:47:41.400
[NORMAL VOICE] It understands.

597
00:47:42.070 --> 00:47:43.230
Activate silence.

598
00:47:47.240 --> 00:47:48.230
[LOW. MUFFLED SPEECH]

599
00:47:59.000 --> 00:48:00.290
[MOHIAM] It must never be known.

600
00:48:01.460 --> 00:48:03.920
[VLADIMIR] There's no satellites
over Arrakis.

601
00:48:04.420 --> 00:48:06.630
The Atreides will die in the dark.

602
00:48:08.050 --> 00:48:09.380
[MOHIAM] On that matter.

603
00:48:09.930 --> 00:48:13.090
Duke Leto Atreides
means nothing to our order.

604
00:48:13.470 --> 00:48:14.930
But his wife is under our protection

605
00:48:15.100 --> 00:48:17.010
and by extension. her son.

606
00:48:17.980 --> 00:48:20.060
Allow them the dignity of exile.

607
00:48:22.230 --> 00:48:23.470
[SIGHS]

608
00:48:24.610 --> 00:48:26.520
House Harkonnen would never dream

609
00:48:26.610 --> 00:48:28.980
of violating the sanctity of your order.

610
00:48:30.530 --> 00:48:31.860
I give you my word.

611
00:48:32.240 --> 00:48:33.530
We will not harm them.

612
00:48:54.220 --> 00:48:55.590
If the Duke's son lives...

613
00:48:55.890 --> 00:48:57.930
No Atreides will live.

614
00:48:58.480 --> 00:49:00.430
My lord. you gave your word
to the witch.

615
00:49:00.810 --> 00:49:01.890
She sees too much.

616
00:49:02.060 --> 00:49:03.650
I said I would not harm them.

617
00:49:03.980 --> 00:49:05.020
And I shall not.

618
00:49:05.400 --> 00:49:07.140
But Arrakis is Arrakis.

619
00:49:08.740 --> 00:49:10.730
And the desert takes the weak.

620
00:49:13.450 --> 00:49:14.610
My desert.

621
00:49:15.540 --> 00:49:17.200
[SINISTER MUSIC PLAYING]

622
00:49:17.410 --> 00:49:18.870
My Arrakis.

623
00:49:21.460 --> 00:49:22.540
My Dune.

624
00:49:26.300 --> 00:49:27.960
[GURNEY] Your first strategy meeting.

625
00:49:28.590 --> 00:49:29.580
Paul Atreides.

626
00:49:29.680 --> 00:49:31.840
who catches hunter-seekers
in his bare hands

627
00:49:31.930 --> 00:49:33.130
like a hero of old.

628
00:49:33.260 --> 00:49:34.750
[LAUGHTER]

629
00:49:35.600 --> 00:49:37.340
[WHISPERS] Thanks
for the humiliation. old man.

630
00:49:37.980 --> 00:49:38.930
Gotta keep an eye on you.

631
00:49:39.980 --> 00:49:41.090
Attention!

632
00:49:49.280 --> 00:49:50.440
Let's get started.

633
00:49:53.160 --> 00:49:54.650
Thufir. Operations.

634
00:49:55.330 --> 00:49:57.610
I secured a copy
of the Harkonnens' account books.

635
00:49:58.370 --> 00:49:59.530
[MEN MURMURING]

636
00:50:00.210 --> 00:50:01.160
The Harkonnens were taking

637
00:50:01.250 --> 00:50:04.040
10 billion solaris
out of here every year.

638
00:50:05.250 --> 00:50:07.580
"They shall suck
of the abundance of the seas.

639
00:50:07.920 --> 00:50:09.250
and the treasure hid in the sand."

640
00:50:09.550 --> 00:50:11.760
[THUFIR] We won't see profits
like that for a while.

641
00:50:12.130 --> 00:50:13.840
Not with the equipment they left us.

642
00:50:14.970 --> 00:50:16.050
How bad is it?

643
00:50:22.480 --> 00:50:24.140
[THUFIR] These are spice silos.

644
00:50:25.860 --> 00:50:27.940
We're meant to fill every crate.

645
00:50:29.150 --> 00:50:30.060
[PAUL] All of them?

646
00:50:30.950 --> 00:50:32.900
Every 25 standard days.

647
00:50:33.950 --> 00:50:35.990
Harkonnen sabotage slows us down.

648
00:50:36.370 --> 00:50:37.820
[PAUL] But who's meant to arbitrate?

649
00:50:37.990 --> 00:50:39.110
Isn't there a Judge of the Change

650
00:50:39.200 --> 00:50:40.410
to oversee the transition?

651
00:50:40.790 --> 00:50:41.780
Who did the Emperor appoint?

652
00:50:42.160 --> 00:50:44.750
Dr. Liet Kynes. Imperial Ecologist.

653
00:50:45.210 --> 00:50:46.290
Been here 20 years.

654
00:50:46.880 --> 00:50:48.330
Eccentric. from what I'm told.

655
00:50:48.750 --> 00:50:50.750
I want to see these
harvesting fields myself.

656
00:50:51.840 --> 00:50:52.880
I wouldn't recommend it. my lord.

657
00:50:53.380 --> 00:50:55.420
Have this Judge of the Change
accompany us.

658
00:50:55.840 --> 00:50:57.080
A meeting's long overdue.

659
00:50:57.510 --> 00:50:59.380
And we'll get a bit
of Imperial protection.

660
00:50:59.640 --> 00:51:01.050
A hostage. [CHUCKLES]

661
00:51:01.180 --> 00:51:02.170
I love it.

662
00:51:02.430 --> 00:51:03.300
Hmm.

663
00:51:03.390 --> 00:51:05.560
- [ENGINE ROARING]
- He's here. my lord.

664
00:51:28.130 --> 00:51:29.620
[DUNCAN WELL-WISHING IN CHAKOBSA]

665
00:51:30.090 --> 00:51:31.580
[IN ENGLISH] Take care of them.
They are friends.

666
00:51:31.920 --> 00:51:32.910
[PAUL] Duncan!

667
00:51:33.220 --> 00:51:34.380
[DUNCAN] Ah! My boy!

668
00:51:34.760 --> 00:51:35.960
[BOTH LAUGHING]

669
00:51:40.010 --> 00:51:41.130
I swear you're getting taller.

670
00:51:41.220 --> 00:51:42.510
[PAUL] Well. you smell much worse.

671
00:51:47.150 --> 00:51:48.600
For four weeks. I lived with the Fremen.

672
00:51:49.020 --> 00:51:51.060
Hidden in the desert.
in a community called a <i>sietch.</i>

673
00:51:51.900 --> 00:51:54.480
Stilgar. the leader of that <i>sietch.</i>
has come with me to meet you. sire.

674
00:51:55.280 --> 00:51:57.110
This <i>sietch.</i> how is it hidden?

675
00:51:57.450 --> 00:51:58.360
It's underground.

676
00:51:58.780 --> 00:52:00.150
Arrakis is filled with caverns.

677
00:52:00.530 --> 00:52:01.570
How big was the place?

678
00:52:02.490 --> 00:52:03.660
I'd say 10.000 people.

679
00:52:04.960 --> 00:52:06.120
And there are hundreds of <i>sietches.</i>

680
00:52:07.540 --> 00:52:09.030
Millions of Fremen.

681
00:52:09.840 --> 00:52:10.830
You were right.

682
00:52:10.960 --> 00:52:14.330
The Harkonnen estimate
was 50.000 on the whole planet.

683
00:52:14.970 --> 00:52:16.670
The Fremen watched me
search for them for days.

684
00:52:17.130 --> 00:52:18.170
I never saw them.

685
00:52:18.930 --> 00:52:20.630
Finally. they sent
a warrior out to kill me.

686
00:52:21.640 --> 00:52:22.550
And I gotta tell you.

687
00:52:23.350 --> 00:52:24.930
I have never come so close to dying.

688
00:52:25.850 --> 00:52:27.510
There's no finer fighter
in the Imperium.

689
00:52:28.560 --> 00:52:29.720
They fight like demons.

690
00:52:30.360 --> 00:52:31.520
Desert power.

691
00:52:34.400 --> 00:52:35.440
Duncan.

692
00:52:36.400 --> 00:52:37.810
- Well done.
- Thank you. my lord.

693
00:52:37.910 --> 00:52:38.900
[MAN] Sire.

694
00:52:39.620 --> 00:52:41.480
Their leader has a knife
he won't surrender. sire.

695
00:52:42.160 --> 00:52:44.370
It's a crysknife.
It's sacred to his people.

696
00:52:45.040 --> 00:52:46.030
Let him pass.

697
00:53:02.720 --> 00:53:03.680
[GURNEY] Stop there.

698
00:53:04.470 --> 00:53:05.840
Hey! Hey!

699
00:53:09.520 --> 00:53:10.510
Mm.

700
00:53:11.400 --> 00:53:12.510
[LETO] Stilgar.

701
00:53:13.480 --> 00:53:14.640
Welcome.

702
00:53:16.190 --> 00:53:18.310
Sir. I respect the personal dignity

703
00:53:18.400 --> 00:53:19.820
of any man that respects mine.

704
00:53:21.660 --> 00:53:23.190
[INHALES DEEPLY]

705
00:53:23.450 --> 00:53:24.440
[STILGAR] Hmm.

706
00:53:25.910 --> 00:53:27.320
[INHALES DEEPLY]

707
00:53:27.790 --> 00:53:28.780
[DUNCAN] Hold.

708
00:53:30.710 --> 00:53:32.160
[CLEARS THROAT] Thank you. Stilgar.

709
00:53:32.710 --> 00:53:35.330
for the gift of your body's moisture.

710
00:53:36.420 --> 00:53:38.250
We accept it in the spirit
in which it was given.

711
00:53:44.180 --> 00:53:45.090
[LETO SNORTS]

712
00:53:46.520 --> 00:53:47.510
[LETO] I'm glad you've come.

713
00:53:48.600 --> 00:53:50.060
I believe your people and mine

714
00:53:50.600 --> 00:53:51.810
have much to offer one another.

715
00:53:51.940 --> 00:53:53.220
No. no. you are Outworlders.

716
00:53:53.400 --> 00:53:54.980
You come here for the spice.

717
00:53:55.070 --> 00:53:57.100
you take it. giving nothing in return.

718
00:53:59.320 --> 00:54:00.310
That's true.

719
00:54:02.610 --> 00:54:05.150
I know you've suffered
at the hands of the Harkonnen.

720
00:54:06.450 --> 00:54:07.530
Name what you want.

721
00:54:08.000 --> 00:54:10.110
If it's in my power to grant.
I'll give it and ask for nothing.

722
00:54:10.250 --> 00:54:13.460
Mm. I ask for this.
Do not seek our <i>sietches.</i>

723
00:54:13.540 --> 00:54:16.160
Do not trespass in our lands.

724
00:54:16.880 --> 00:54:19.870
The desert was ours
long before you came.

725
00:54:20.050 --> 00:54:22.880
So. come and dig your spice.
but when you have it.

726
00:54:22.970 --> 00:54:25.340
go back to this side of the Shield Wall

727
00:54:25.510 --> 00:54:27.420
and leave the desert to the Fremen.

728
00:54:27.600 --> 00:54:30.180
You will address the Duke
as "my lord" or "sire."

729
00:54:30.270 --> 00:54:32.010
[LETO] Gurney. just...
just a moment.

730
00:54:32.940 --> 00:54:34.100
The Emperor

731
00:54:34.480 --> 00:54:36.850
has given me Arrakis as my fief

732
00:54:37.360 --> 00:54:38.640
to rule and protect.

733
00:54:39.190 --> 00:54:41.310
I cannot promise
not to travel into the desert

734
00:54:41.490 --> 00:54:43.070
if duty compels me.

735
00:54:44.660 --> 00:54:46.520
But your <i>sietches</i> will be yours forever.

736
00:54:47.910 --> 00:54:49.900
And you will never be hunted
while I govern here.

737
00:54:54.750 --> 00:54:55.960
That's very honorable.

738
00:54:56.960 --> 00:54:59.200
I must go. That's all
I have to say to you.

739
00:54:59.420 --> 00:55:00.380
[PAUL] Won't you stay?

740
00:55:01.380 --> 00:55:02.420
We would honor you.

741
00:55:03.260 --> 00:55:05.470
Honor requires that I be elsewhere.

742
00:55:06.800 --> 00:55:07.790
[SPEAKING CHAKOBSA]

743
00:55:17.770 --> 00:55:18.810
I don't like him.

744
00:55:19.150 --> 00:55:21.140
Our plan bears fruit.

745
00:55:21.440 --> 00:55:22.560
But it will take time?

746
00:55:23.030 --> 00:55:23.980
Yes.

747
00:55:25.160 --> 00:55:27.020
It will take time.

748
00:55:30.160 --> 00:55:31.370
Here. this is for you.

749
00:55:35.540 --> 00:55:36.580
It's a paracompass.

750
00:55:37.750 --> 00:55:39.830
The moons here
have a magnetic field. so...

751
00:55:40.340 --> 00:55:41.870
a simple compass needle
won't point north.

752
00:55:43.170 --> 00:55:44.880
Takes a clever piece
of clockwork to sort it out.

753
00:55:45.260 --> 00:55:46.420
[PAUL] The Fremen make these?

754
00:55:47.260 --> 00:55:48.720
And stillsuits. and sand compactors.

755
00:55:48.800 --> 00:55:50.040
and all kinds of ingenious things.

756
00:55:50.390 --> 00:55:52.100
[GURNEY] What the hell
is a sand compactor?

757
00:55:54.640 --> 00:55:55.630
[DUNCAN] That's a sand compactor.

758
00:55:55.850 --> 00:55:56.720
[ALL CHUCKLE]

759
00:55:57.100 --> 00:55:59.190
My God. man. you've gone native.

760
00:55:59.820 --> 00:56:00.770
You admire them.

761
00:56:02.440 --> 00:56:03.350
I do.

762
00:56:04.240 --> 00:56:05.940
They're fierce but loyal.

763
00:56:06.820 --> 00:56:08.030
They're attuned to the desert.

764
00:56:08.620 --> 00:56:09.480
Part of it.

765
00:56:10.080 --> 00:56:11.070
It's part of them.

766
00:56:12.290 --> 00:56:13.200
You wait till you see it.

767
00:56:14.290 --> 00:56:15.240
It's beautiful out there.

768
00:56:18.960 --> 00:56:20.670
[ANNOUNCER] <i>Sunrise warning.
all workers.</i>

769
00:56:21.090 --> 00:56:23.620
<i>Temperature today
will reach 140 degrees.</i>

770
00:56:23.800 --> 00:56:25.660
<i>We are currently 90 degrees.</i>

771
00:56:25.760 --> 00:56:28.880
<i>and in 10 minutes.
we will hit 120 degrees.</i>

772
00:56:30.050 --> 00:56:31.290
<i>Last warning call.</i>

773
00:56:31.390 --> 00:56:32.880
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

774
00:56:46.110 --> 00:56:47.730
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

775
00:57:05.210 --> 00:57:06.670
The Judge of the Change. sire.

776
00:57:07.300 --> 00:57:08.330
Dr. Liet Kynes.

777
00:57:09.090 --> 00:57:10.250
My lord Duke.

778
00:57:11.510 --> 00:57:12.500
Welcome to Arrakis.

779
00:57:13.350 --> 00:57:14.710
[PAUL] You're the Imperial Ecologist.

780
00:57:15.390 --> 00:57:16.760
Thank you for the stillsuits.

781
00:57:17.350 --> 00:57:18.640
They are of Fremen make.

782
00:57:19.310 --> 00:57:20.140
The best.

783
00:57:20.480 --> 00:57:21.690
With your permission. sire.

784
00:57:21.770 --> 00:57:23.010
I must check
the integrity of your suit--

785
00:57:23.610 --> 00:57:24.640
[LETO] Whoa.

786
00:57:25.110 --> 00:57:26.100
It's all right.

787
00:57:28.320 --> 00:57:29.360
It's all right.

788
00:57:30.240 --> 00:57:33.610
[CHUCKLES LIGHTLY] Dr. Kynes.
we're in your hands.

789
00:57:38.580 --> 00:57:42.700
A stillsuit is a high-efficiency
filtration system.

790
00:57:43.920 --> 00:57:45.460
Even this early in the morning.

791
00:57:45.630 --> 00:57:47.960
you wouldn't survive two hours
without one of these.

792
00:57:49.260 --> 00:57:50.210
It cools the body

793
00:57:51.760 --> 00:57:54.090
and recycles
the water lost to sweat.

794
00:57:55.640 --> 00:57:57.880
Your body's movements
provide the power.

795
00:57:58.930 --> 00:58:00.270
Inside the mask. you'll find a tube

796
00:58:00.350 --> 00:58:02.590
to allow you to drink
the recycled water.

797
00:58:02.730 --> 00:58:03.720
[LETO] Mm.

798
00:58:03.860 --> 00:58:05.310
In good working order.
your suit won't lose

799
00:58:05.400 --> 00:58:07.190
more than a thimbleful of water a day.

800
00:58:07.860 --> 00:58:08.770
[LETO] Most impressive.

801
00:58:11.110 --> 00:58:12.190
Let's have a look at you. lad.

802
00:58:14.700 --> 00:58:15.740
You've...

803
00:58:16.370 --> 00:58:17.360
worn a stillsuit before?

804
00:58:17.450 --> 00:58:18.570
No. this is my first time.

805
00:58:21.500 --> 00:58:24.080
Your desert boots are fitted
slip-fashion at the ankles.

806
00:58:24.210 --> 00:58:25.200
Who taught you to do that?

807
00:58:26.090 --> 00:58:27.200
It seemed the right way.

808
00:58:29.340 --> 00:58:30.330
[SPEAKING CHAKOBSA]

809
00:58:35.550 --> 00:58:36.590
[IN ENGLISH] Are you Fremen?

810
00:58:38.680 --> 00:58:41.550
I am accepted
in both <i>sietch</i> and village.

811
00:58:42.690 --> 00:58:47.560
Now. come and see the spice sands
on which your livelihood depends.

812
00:58:52.860 --> 00:58:54.850
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

813
00:59:26.020 --> 00:59:26.930
What would you do

814
00:59:27.020 --> 00:59:28.560
if your ornithopter went down out here?

815
00:59:29.320 --> 00:59:30.770
You wouldn't want
to go down out there.

816
00:59:31.780 --> 00:59:32.770
It's worm territory.

817
00:59:35.700 --> 00:59:36.690
Dust cloud.

818
00:59:37.740 --> 00:59:38.730
[LETO] I see it.

819
00:59:40.700 --> 00:59:42.240
That's one of your harvesters.

820
00:59:45.170 --> 00:59:46.450
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

821
01:00:00.100 --> 01:00:01.930
[MACHINERY CLUNKING]

822
01:00:08.360 --> 01:00:09.440
[DR. KYNES] You can see the spice

823
01:00:09.520 --> 01:00:10.640
scattered over the surface.

824
01:00:12.860 --> 01:00:14.220
A rich spice bed

825
01:00:14.950 --> 01:00:16.190
by the color.

826
01:00:16.360 --> 01:00:18.700
If you get a little higher.
you'll have a better view.

827
01:00:33.880 --> 01:00:36.170
You see these spotter aircraft
looking for wormsign.

828
01:00:38.220 --> 01:00:39.210
[PAUL] Wormsign?

829
01:00:39.760 --> 01:00:41.720
A sand wave
moving toward the crawler.

830
01:00:42.350 --> 01:00:44.300
Worms travel deep but get closer

831
01:00:44.390 --> 01:00:45.630
to the surface when they attack.

832
01:00:46.690 --> 01:00:47.930
If you are patient.

833
01:00:49.150 --> 01:00:50.310
we should see one.

834
01:00:51.230 --> 01:00:52.390
A worm always comes?

835
01:00:52.730 --> 01:00:55.140
Always. They're drawn
by rhythmic noises.

836
01:00:55.780 --> 01:00:57.270
[PAUL] Why don't we just
shield the crawlers?

837
01:00:57.780 --> 01:00:59.900
A shield's a death sentence
in the desert.

838
01:01:00.410 --> 01:01:01.520
It attracts the worms

839
01:01:01.660 --> 01:01:03.900
and drives them into a killing frenzy.

840
01:01:06.790 --> 01:01:07.780
Is that a worm?

841
01:01:20.220 --> 01:01:21.300
[DR. KYNES] Big one.

842
01:01:22.140 --> 01:01:23.250
You have good eyes.

843
01:01:24.640 --> 01:01:26.550
Calling crawler Delta Ajax niner.

844
01:01:26.930 --> 01:01:28.550
Wormsign warning. Acknowledge.

845
01:01:29.480 --> 01:01:31.560
[CRAWLER OVER RADIO]
<i>Who calls Delta Ajax niner?</i>

846
01:01:32.060 --> 01:01:33.050
<i>Over.</i>

847
01:01:33.150 --> 01:01:34.600
They seem pretty calm about it.

848
01:01:34.770 --> 01:01:37.180
[DR. KYNES] Unlisted flight.
Imperium business.

849
01:01:37.490 --> 01:01:39.350
Wormsign north and east of you.

850
01:01:39.820 --> 01:01:41.150
3.7 kilometers.

851
01:01:41.740 --> 01:01:43.070
[SPOTTER OVER RADIO]
<i>Delta Ajax niner.</i>

852
01:01:43.160 --> 01:01:44.990
<i>this is Spotter One.
Wormsign confirmed.</i>

853
01:01:46.490 --> 01:01:48.240
<i>Stand by for contact fix.</i>

854
01:01:52.460 --> 01:01:54.790
<i>Worm is on intercept course
to your position.</i>

855
01:01:54.960 --> 01:01:56.450
<i>Contact in five minutes.</i>

856
01:01:56.630 --> 01:01:58.210
So. what happens now?

857
01:01:58.630 --> 01:02:00.620
They'll call a carryall
to lift the crawler.

858
01:02:01.380 --> 01:02:03.170
They'll harvest right up
to the last minute.

859
01:02:03.470 --> 01:02:04.930
[CRAWLER] <i>Calling carryall Alpha Zero.</i>

860
01:02:05.100 --> 01:02:06.550
<i>Ready for docking sequence.</i>

861
01:02:07.020 --> 01:02:09.100
<i>Contact five minutes. Over.</i>

862
01:02:14.110 --> 01:02:15.850
[SPOTTER] <i>Anybody got a visual
on the carryall?</i>

863
01:02:20.450 --> 01:02:21.440
[DR. KYNES] There it is.

864
01:02:21.530 --> 01:02:23.070
[CARRYALL OVER RADIO]
<i>This is carryall Alpha Zero</i>

865
01:02:23.160 --> 01:02:24.490
<i>to Delta Ajax niner.</i>

866
01:02:25.830 --> 01:02:27.160
<i>Approaching from your east.</i>

867
01:02:27.990 --> 01:02:30.700
<i>Correcting altitude
and preparing docking equipment.</i>

868
01:02:30.870 --> 01:02:33.740
[CRAWLER] <i>Copy. Alpha Zero.
Initiating docking sequence.</i>

869
01:02:36.540 --> 01:02:37.580
[CARRYALL] <i>T-5.</i>

870
01:02:37.750 --> 01:02:38.740
[MAN] <i>Copy that.</i>

871
01:02:38.920 --> 01:02:40.380
[CRAWLER] <i>Prepare to be airborne
in 30 seconds.</i>

872
01:02:40.550 --> 01:02:43.130
[CARRYALL] <i>Docking sequence initiated.
Brace yourselves.</i>

873
01:02:45.140 --> 01:02:46.380
[EXPLOSION]

874
01:02:46.470 --> 01:02:48.680
[MAN] <i>Alpha Zero. we're short
one point of contact.</i>

875
01:02:49.020 --> 01:02:50.260
[CRAWLER] <i>What is going on?</i>

876
01:02:50.430 --> 01:02:52.270
[CARRYALL] <i>It's one of the anchors.
It's dead.</i>

877
01:02:53.480 --> 01:02:54.510
[DR. KYNES] Shit.

878
01:02:55.110 --> 01:02:57.100
[CARRYALL] <i>Carryall unable to proceed.</i>

879
01:02:57.190 --> 01:02:58.930
<i>Unable to lift without that anchor.</i>

880
01:02:59.110 --> 01:03:00.820
[CRAWLER] <i>All call! All call!</i>

881
01:03:01.280 --> 01:03:03.390
<i>Any carryall in the sector.
please respond!</i>

882
01:03:04.030 --> 01:03:05.900
<i>Spotter One.
give us an update. Over.</i>

883
01:03:05.990 --> 01:03:06.950
[CARRYALL] <i>Hydraulics are dead.</i>

884
01:03:07.030 --> 01:03:08.110
<i>We won't make it.
You have to evacuate.</i>

885
01:03:08.200 --> 01:03:09.240
[ANNOUNCER OVER RADIO]
<i>Contact in four minutes.</i>

886
01:03:09.330 --> 01:03:10.320
[CRAWLER] <i>Try it again!</i>

887
01:03:10.410 --> 01:03:11.450
How many men on that crawler?

888
01:03:11.960 --> 01:03:12.820
Crew of 21.

889
01:03:13.250 --> 01:03:14.490
[LETO] Our ships can take six each.

890
01:03:14.670 --> 01:03:15.700
That's still three short.

891
01:03:16.460 --> 01:03:17.450
We'll find a way.

892
01:03:29.760 --> 01:03:31.600
[OVER RADIO] <i>This is Duke Leto Atreides.</i>

893
01:03:32.390 --> 01:03:35.430
<i>We're coming down to extract
the crew of Delta Ajax niner.</i>

894
01:03:35.940 --> 01:03:37.050
<i>We'll set down on the west.</i>

895
01:03:48.410 --> 01:03:50.020
Shield generators
weigh 100 kilos each.

896
01:03:50.830 --> 01:03:51.820
Yes. Gurney.

897
01:03:51.910 --> 01:03:53.570
have our escorts throw out
the shield generators.

898
01:03:53.870 --> 01:03:54.860
[GURNEY] Yes. sire.

899
01:03:54.960 --> 01:03:56.790
[LETO] And. Paul. I want you
at the back of the thopter.

900
01:03:56.960 --> 01:03:57.950
Guide them in.

901
01:03:58.130 --> 01:03:59.410
Delta Ajax niner.

902
01:03:59.500 --> 01:04:01.740
put seven men each in my ships now.

903
01:04:02.300 --> 01:04:03.660
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

904
01:04:28.570 --> 01:04:30.360
[ETHEREAL MUSIC PLAYING]

905
01:04:47.050 --> 01:04:48.760
[MACHINERY CLANKING]

906
01:05:00.400 --> 01:05:01.760
[ANNOUNCER OVER RADIO]
<i>Contact in two minutes.</i>

907
01:05:02.690 --> 01:05:04.180
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

908
01:05:04.690 --> 01:05:06.900
[SPOTTER] <i>Getting close. guys.
We better abandon ship now.</i>

909
01:05:07.450 --> 01:05:08.730
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

910
01:05:09.570 --> 01:05:10.560
Where are they?

911
01:05:10.740 --> 01:05:13.070
[CRAWLER] <i>Sir. there's protocol
for a reason.</i>

912
01:05:13.240 --> 01:05:15.450
<i>If we take one step out there.
we're as good as dead.</i>

913
01:05:16.040 --> 01:05:17.650
<i>Besides. we've got a full load of spice.</i>

914
01:05:17.750 --> 01:05:19.410
<i>- We can't just leave it.</i>
- Damn the spice!

915
01:05:20.080 --> 01:05:22.120
I want every man off that crawler now!

916
01:05:26.010 --> 01:05:27.670
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

917
01:05:36.140 --> 01:05:37.130
Hey!

918
01:05:37.430 --> 01:05:38.420
Hey!

919
01:05:38.810 --> 01:05:40.640
Seven over here. seven over there.

920
01:05:43.310 --> 01:05:44.980
Go! Go! Go!

921
01:05:45.530 --> 01:05:46.730
[TENSE MUSIC STOPS]

922
01:05:48.900 --> 01:05:50.520
[ETHEREAL MUSIC PLAYING]

923
01:05:58.410 --> 01:05:59.820
[EERIE VOICES MURMUR]

924
01:06:00.750 --> 01:06:03.080
[EERIE VOICES] Kwisatz Haderach.

925
01:06:05.250 --> 01:06:07.420
[EERIE VOICES MURMURING INDISTINCTLY]

926
01:06:16.510 --> 01:06:19.970
Kwisatz Haderach <i>awakes.</i>

927
01:06:20.060 --> 01:06:21.520
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

928
01:06:29.490 --> 01:06:30.820
[GURNEY] Hurry! Get on!

929
01:06:30.900 --> 01:06:32.390
[MEN SHOUT HURRIEDLY]

930
01:06:39.660 --> 01:06:40.650
[DR. KYNES] It's here!

931
01:06:43.710 --> 01:06:44.700
[GURNEY] Paul!

932
01:06:47.210 --> 01:06:48.200
Paul!

933
01:06:52.260 --> 01:06:55.470
[QUIETLY] I recognize
your footsteps. old man.

934
01:06:56.350 --> 01:06:57.340
Get up!

935
01:06:58.060 --> 01:06:59.050
Let's go!

936
01:07:00.640 --> 01:07:02.630
What's the matter with you?
Come on! Let's go!

937
01:07:03.270 --> 01:07:04.260
Run!

938
01:07:05.520 --> 01:07:06.930
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

939
01:07:13.240 --> 01:07:14.100
[GRUNTING]

940
01:07:30.340 --> 01:07:31.330
[GURNEY] Hey!

941
01:07:49.980 --> 01:07:51.390
Bless the Maker and His Water.

942
01:07:52.530 --> 01:07:54.440
Bless the coming and going of Him.

943
01:07:54.900 --> 01:07:57.070
May His passage cleanse the world

944
01:07:57.780 --> 01:07:59.650
and keep the world for His people.

945
01:08:10.040 --> 01:08:11.660
[SANDWORM ROARS]

946
01:08:23.930 --> 01:08:24.920
Hey!

947
01:08:25.020 --> 01:08:27.430
- You cannot take such risks.
- [PAUL] Yes. sir.

948
01:08:27.520 --> 01:08:28.510
You have responsibilities.

949
01:08:28.610 --> 01:08:29.890
I... I'm sorry. sir.
It won't happen again.

950
01:08:29.980 --> 01:08:30.890
Go.

951
01:08:31.860 --> 01:08:32.810
Dr. Kynes.

952
01:08:35.150 --> 01:08:36.190
You saw it.

953
01:08:36.860 --> 01:08:38.700
With your own eyes. It's plain to see.

954
01:08:38.870 --> 01:08:40.950
Everything they've left us
is in shambles.

955
01:08:41.490 --> 01:08:42.480
We've been set up to fail.

956
01:08:43.450 --> 01:08:45.160
That carryall was just old.

957
01:08:46.370 --> 01:08:48.280
The desert isn't kind to equipment.

958
01:08:50.130 --> 01:08:51.410
You know what will happen

959
01:08:51.880 --> 01:08:53.960
if I don't get spice
production back on track.

960
01:08:54.260 --> 01:08:55.340
[SCOFFS]

961
01:08:56.420 --> 01:08:59.170
I'm not here to take your part.

962
01:09:00.260 --> 01:09:03.850
Arrakis has seen men like you
come and go.

963
01:09:06.850 --> 01:09:10.440
Take good care of your family.

964
01:09:13.860 --> 01:09:16.230
The desert's not kind
to humans either.

965
01:09:33.630 --> 01:09:35.870
Spice is a psychoactive chemical.

966
01:09:37.760 --> 01:09:39.370
You seem to be sensitive.

967
01:09:43.850 --> 01:09:44.840
You'll be fine.

968
01:09:46.600 --> 01:09:48.220
Thank you. Dr. Yueh.

969
01:09:58.280 --> 01:10:00.060
That wasn't an allergic reaction.

970
01:10:02.490 --> 01:10:03.700
I had a vision.

971
01:10:06.790 --> 01:10:08.240
My eyes were wide open.

972
01:10:10.330 --> 01:10:11.320
What did you see?

973
01:10:18.170 --> 01:10:20.160
[EERIE ETHEREAL MUSIC PLAYING]

974
01:10:49.160 --> 01:10:52.500
[EERIE VOICES] Kwisatz Haderach.

975
01:10:52.960 --> 01:10:55.240
<i>You can</i> see.

976
01:11:37.500 --> 01:11:38.740
<i>[PAUL] It's confusing.</i>

977
01:11:39.170 --> 01:11:40.330
<i>I thought I saw my death.</i>

978
01:11:40.510 --> 01:11:41.790
<i>only it wasn't.</i>

979
01:11:43.220 --> 01:11:46.430
<i>I know a knife is important. somehow.</i>

980
01:11:48.930 --> 01:11:50.800
<i>Someone will hand me a blade.</i>

981
01:11:51.560 --> 01:11:54.680
<i>but I don't know who.
or when. or where.</i>

982
01:11:57.270 --> 01:11:59.930
<i>Some things. though. are crystal clear.</i>

983
01:12:00.070 --> 01:12:01.060
<i>I can feel it.</i>

984
01:12:06.320 --> 01:12:07.440
<i>I know you're pregnant.</i>

985
01:12:13.660 --> 01:12:14.950
You can't know that.

986
01:12:16.960 --> 01:12:18.070
I barely know that.

987
01:12:18.250 --> 01:12:19.830
It's only been a few weeks.

988
01:12:30.640 --> 01:12:33.050
[PRIEST THROAT-SINGING IN SARDAUKAR]

989
01:13:03.090 --> 01:13:04.420
[BASHAR SPEAKING SARDAUKAR]

990
01:13:11.350 --> 01:13:12.550
[PITER IN ENGLISH] Atreides legions

991
01:13:12.640 --> 01:13:14.130
are the finest in the Imperium.

992
01:13:15.100 --> 01:13:17.470
Trained by Gurney Halleck
and Duncan Idaho.

993
01:13:17.560 --> 01:13:18.550
[SPEAKING SARDAUKAR]

994
01:13:25.860 --> 01:13:27.230
[IN ENGLISH] Just so.

995
01:13:28.400 --> 01:13:29.640
Three battalions.

996
01:13:29.990 --> 01:13:31.070
As agreed.

997
01:13:31.160 --> 01:13:32.650
[CONTINUES THROAT-SINGING]

998
01:13:34.240 --> 01:13:35.230
[ALL GRUNT]

999
01:13:35.490 --> 01:13:36.480
[SPEAKING SARDAUKAR]

1000
01:13:46.550 --> 01:13:48.710
[WHIMPERING]

1001
01:13:54.180 --> 01:13:56.170
[CRYING SOFTLY]

1002
01:14:11.820 --> 01:14:13.690
There is something
you need to know about Paul.

1003
01:14:14.200 --> 01:14:15.070
[LETO] No.

1004
01:14:15.870 --> 01:14:17.280
Don't think I want to know.

1005
01:14:18.540 --> 01:14:20.280
Ever since you brought him
before your Reverend Mother.

1006
01:14:20.460 --> 01:14:21.740
he hasn't been the same.

1007
01:14:23.920 --> 01:14:25.030
He's distracted.

1008
01:14:27.250 --> 01:14:29.960
Jessica. you gave me a son.

1009
01:14:30.510 --> 01:14:31.750
And from the moment he was born.

1010
01:14:31.840 --> 01:14:33.630
I never questioned you.

1011
01:14:33.800 --> 01:14:35.510
I trusted you completely.

1012
01:14:36.560 --> 01:14:38.170
Even when you walked in shadows.

1013
01:14:39.730 --> 01:14:41.430
Now I'm asking you this one thing.

1014
01:14:44.270 --> 01:14:45.560
If anything happens...

1015
01:14:47.650 --> 01:14:48.810
will you protect our son?

1016
01:14:50.740 --> 01:14:52.150
With my life.

1017
01:14:52.240 --> 01:14:54.450
I'm not asking his mother.
I'm asking the Bene Gesserit.

1018
01:14:59.160 --> 01:15:00.280
Will you protect Paul?

1019
01:15:06.750 --> 01:15:08.410
Why are you having these thoughts?

1020
01:15:15.140 --> 01:15:17.090
Leto. this is not you.

1021
01:15:23.310 --> 01:15:24.930
I thought we'd have more time.

1022
01:15:44.710 --> 01:15:46.490
[DR. YUEH] Have a good night.
Master Paul.

1023
01:15:47.420 --> 01:15:48.780
[PAUL] Good night. Dr. Yueh.

1024
01:15:58.680 --> 01:15:59.890
[LADY JESSICA] <i>You need to sleep.</i>

1025
01:16:01.560 --> 01:16:02.760
No.

1026
01:16:03.060 --> 01:16:04.170
Not like that.

1027
01:16:07.400 --> 01:16:08.760
[LETO SIGHS DEEPLY]

1028
01:16:20.030 --> 01:16:21.520
I should have married you.

1029
01:16:26.920 --> 01:16:28.330
[FOOTSTEPS]

1030
01:16:29.920 --> 01:16:31.130
[WEAPON FIRING]

1031
01:16:33.010 --> 01:16:34.340
[GUARDS GROANING]

1032
01:16:40.010 --> 01:16:41.220
[WHEEZING]

1033
01:16:49.110 --> 01:16:50.560
[SHIELD POWERING DOWN]

1034
01:16:57.450 --> 01:16:58.780
[LOW TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

1035
01:17:32.570 --> 01:17:33.730
[SOFT GRUNT]

1036
01:17:40.450 --> 01:17:41.810
[SOFTLY] Hawat. Security.

1037
01:17:44.490 --> 01:17:45.570
[NORMAL TONE] Security.

1038
01:17:54.250 --> 01:17:55.460
[DEVICE BEEPS]

1039
01:18:00.430 --> 01:18:02.260
[CHOKING]

1040
01:18:08.480 --> 01:18:09.560
[STIFLED GRUNT]

1041
01:18:13.810 --> 01:18:14.800
[DART FIRES]

1042
01:18:14.900 --> 01:18:16.640
[SHIELD CRACKLING]

1043
01:18:24.910 --> 01:18:26.740
[GROANING]

1044
01:18:35.250 --> 01:18:36.540
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

1045
01:18:38.670 --> 01:18:39.750
[WHIMPERS]

1046
01:18:48.890 --> 01:18:50.130
[LIEUTENANT] Sir. Sir.

1047
01:18:51.520 --> 01:18:52.720
The shield's come down.

1048
01:18:53.480 --> 01:18:54.970
- [ALARM BLARING]
- [SOLDIERS CLAMORING]

1049
01:19:02.320 --> 01:19:03.310
[GURNEY] God in heaven.

1050
01:19:04.240 --> 01:19:06.480
Get everything with guns
off the ground! Go!

1051
01:19:06.870 --> 01:19:07.980
[SOLDIERS SHOUTING]

1052
01:19:09.290 --> 01:19:10.740
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

1053
01:19:12.960 --> 01:19:14.040
[MISSILE WHISTLES]

1054
01:19:51.160 --> 01:19:52.320
Go! Go! Go!

1055
01:19:54.040 --> 01:19:55.070
[SOLDIERS SCREAMING]

1056
01:20:15.230 --> 01:20:16.340
[MISSILE WHISTLES]

1057
01:20:49.260 --> 01:20:50.380
[GRUNTING]

1058
01:20:52.890 --> 01:20:54.010
[GROANS]

1059
01:20:54.890 --> 01:20:56.800
With me! With me!

1060
01:20:57.560 --> 01:20:58.800
[SOLDIERS YELLING]

1061
01:21:00.650 --> 01:21:01.760
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

1062
01:21:22.800 --> 01:21:24.130
[MARCHING FOOTSTEPS]

1063
01:21:25.960 --> 01:21:26.950
[LIEUTENANT] Atreides!

1064
01:21:27.170 --> 01:21:28.160
[GUARDS] Atreides!

1065
01:21:32.260 --> 01:21:33.670
[ALL GRUNTING IN UNISON]

1066
01:21:35.810 --> 01:21:37.390
[SYNCHRONIZED GRUNTING]

1067
01:21:40.940 --> 01:21:42.270
[ALL GRUNTING]

1068
01:21:57.370 --> 01:21:59.200
- [ATREIDES GUARD 1] Sardaukar!
- [ATREIDES GUARD 2] Sardaukar!

1069
01:22:02.790 --> 01:22:04.030
[GROANING]

1070
01:22:22.520 --> 01:22:23.890
I'm sorry. my lord.

1071
01:22:27.190 --> 01:22:29.400
But I've made a bargain
with the Baron.

1072
01:22:30.360 --> 01:22:31.650
[LETO BREATHING RAGGEDLY]

1073
01:22:32.530 --> 01:22:33.520
Why?

1074
01:22:34.450 --> 01:22:35.860
I had no choice.

1075
01:22:36.950 --> 01:22:38.820
The Harkonnens have my wife. Wanna.

1076
01:22:40.790 --> 01:22:42.780
They take her apart like a doll.

1077
01:22:44.080 --> 01:22:45.450
I will buy her freedom.

1078
01:22:46.250 --> 01:22:47.330
And you are the price.

1079
01:22:51.260 --> 01:22:54.050
For Paul. I will do what I can.

1080
01:22:54.890 --> 01:22:56.170
And you

1081
01:22:56.760 --> 01:22:58.090
will kill a man for me.

1082
01:23:03.100 --> 01:23:06.270
I'm going to replace your peg tooth.

1083
01:23:06.770 --> 01:23:10.230
If you bite down hard.
this tooth will crush.

1084
01:23:11.990 --> 01:23:15.400
Breathe out. and you will
fill the air with poison.

1085
01:23:16.330 --> 01:23:17.990
It will be your last breath.

1086
01:23:18.950 --> 01:23:20.820
But if you choose your moment well.

1087
01:23:22.540 --> 01:23:24.200
it will also be the Baron's.

1088
01:23:43.100 --> 01:23:44.470
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

1089
01:24:02.870 --> 01:24:03.860
[YELLING]

1090
01:24:24.890 --> 01:24:26.300
[SOLDIERS SPEAK INDISTINCTLY]

1091
01:24:35.490 --> 01:24:36.570
[SOLDIER GROANS]

1092
01:24:39.490 --> 01:24:40.480
[GRUNTS]

1093
01:24:58.470 --> 01:24:59.550
Paul.

1094
01:25:10.150 --> 01:25:11.730
[DOOR CLOSES]

1095
01:25:12.270 --> 01:25:13.260
[TROOPER 1 SPEAKING HARKONNEN]

1096
01:25:19.820 --> 01:25:20.810
[TROOPER 2 SPEAKING]

1097
01:25:23.240 --> 01:25:24.230
[TROOPER 1 SPEAKING]

1098
01:25:37.420 --> 01:25:38.410
[IN SIGN LANGUAGE]

1099
01:26:15.210 --> 01:26:17.170
[ALL GRUNTING]

1100
01:26:22.510 --> 01:26:23.630
[DUNCAN] To hell. dogs!

1101
01:26:26.010 --> 01:26:27.100
[GRUNTS]

1102
01:26:44.830 --> 01:26:45.780
[ALARM BEEPING]

1103
01:27:59.650 --> 01:28:01.730
[TROOPER 1 IN ENGLISH]
I've never had a highborn.

1104
01:28:04.610 --> 01:28:05.600
You?

1105
01:28:06.160 --> 01:28:07.650
Bene Gesserit ain't all highborn.

1106
01:28:08.660 --> 01:28:10.650
[TROOPER 1] She's highborn
enough for me.

1107
01:28:12.200 --> 01:28:13.990
Let's feed the kid to the worms.

1108
01:28:14.540 --> 01:28:16.280
And give her a long goodbye.

1109
01:28:16.580 --> 01:28:18.420
Don't you dare touch my mother.

1110
01:28:19.840 --> 01:28:20.790
Don't talk.

1111
01:28:25.840 --> 01:28:26.830
[IN SIGN LANGUAGE]

1112
01:28:29.810 --> 01:28:30.800
[PAUL SIGHS]

1113
01:28:32.560 --> 01:28:33.800
[STERNLY] Remove her gag.

1114
01:28:41.730 --> 01:28:42.560
[RETCHES]

1115
01:28:43.280 --> 01:28:44.360
[TROOPER 1] Shut up.

1116
01:28:45.030 --> 01:28:45.890
[IN SIGN LANGUAGE]

1117
01:28:48.320 --> 01:28:49.530
[PANTING]

1118
01:28:53.950 --> 01:28:54.940
[TROOPER 1 SPEAKING HARKONNEN]

1119
01:28:59.630 --> 01:29:00.460
[PAUL BREATHING DEEPLY]

1120
01:29:13.600 --> 01:29:14.930
[DISTORTED VOICE] Remove her gag.

1121
01:29:21.190 --> 01:29:22.180
[DISTORTED VOICE] Kill him.

1122
01:29:31.280 --> 01:29:32.320
[DISTORTED VOICE] Set us free.

1123
01:29:37.750 --> 01:29:40.160
[SPEAKING HARKONNEN]

1124
01:29:41.960 --> 01:29:43.000
[TROOPER 1 GROANS]

1125
01:29:44.300 --> 01:29:45.710
[LADY JESSICA GRUNTING]

1126
01:29:45.960 --> 01:29:46.920
[DISTORTED VOICE] Stop!

1127
01:29:47.630 --> 01:29:48.750
Cut the rope.

1128
01:29:51.640 --> 01:29:52.630
Give me the knife.

1129
01:29:53.640 --> 01:29:54.880
[STABS]

1130
01:29:57.310 --> 01:29:58.300
[GRUNTS]

1131
01:30:01.900 --> 01:30:04.480
[NORMAL VOICE]
Your pitch was too forced.

1132
01:30:12.780 --> 01:30:13.990
[PAUL] It's a fremkit.

1133
01:30:18.500 --> 01:30:20.280
[MAN SPEAKS HARKONNEN OVER RADIO]

1134
01:30:25.050 --> 01:30:26.250
[ENGINE SHUTS OFF]

1135
01:30:27.340 --> 01:30:28.370
They've crippled the ship.

1136
01:30:44.150 --> 01:30:45.890
[DISTANT EXPLOSIONS]

1137
01:30:53.910 --> 01:30:55.190
[GASPING]

1138
01:31:00.210 --> 01:31:01.410
[SIGHS]

1139
01:31:17.350 --> 01:31:18.510
[EXPLOSIONS CONTINUE]

1140
01:31:37.200 --> 01:31:38.280
[WHEEZING SOFTLY]

1141
01:31:40.870 --> 01:31:41.860
[MAN] Mmm.

1142
01:31:48.920 --> 01:31:49.960
[VLADIMIR GRUNTS SOFTLY]

1143
01:31:53.050 --> 01:31:54.380
[CUTLERY CLINKING]

1144
01:31:54.470 --> 01:31:55.580
[VLADIMIR GRUNTS]

1145
01:32:00.850 --> 01:32:01.840
Ah.

1146
01:32:02.430 --> 01:32:03.420
[MUNCHING]

1147
01:32:04.020 --> 01:32:06.260
You have a wonderful kitchen. cousin.

1148
01:32:08.060 --> 01:32:09.300
[WIND HOWLING]

1149
01:32:14.320 --> 01:32:15.530
[PAUL GRUNTS]

1150
01:32:25.290 --> 01:32:27.000
This is Dr. Yueh's handwriting.

1151
01:32:28.250 --> 01:32:30.120
"If anyone makes it out
of Arrakeen alive.

1152
01:32:30.670 --> 01:32:32.460
there's an Atreides beacon
in the fremkit.

1153
01:32:33.050 --> 01:32:34.630
God willing.
they'll be able to find you."

1154
01:32:39.220 --> 01:32:40.710
[WHEEZING WEAKLY]

1155
01:32:43.060 --> 01:32:44.050
My lord Baron.

1156
01:32:45.480 --> 01:32:46.640
Dr. Yueh.

1157
01:32:46.810 --> 01:32:47.970
[VLADIMIR] The traitor.

1158
01:32:49.650 --> 01:32:50.730
What do you want?

1159
01:32:51.980 --> 01:32:53.440
I jammed their comms

1160
01:32:54.360 --> 01:32:55.850
and lowered their shields.

1161
01:32:56.360 --> 01:32:57.400
[VLADIMIR] Hmm.

1162
01:32:57.490 --> 01:32:59.610
[DR. YUEH] I delivered
the Duke and his family.

1163
01:33:00.160 --> 01:33:01.770
[VLADIMIR] The bargain to the letter.

1164
01:33:02.700 --> 01:33:03.820
And what was I to do for you?

1165
01:33:05.330 --> 01:33:07.320
Deliver my wife from her agony.

1166
01:33:09.330 --> 01:33:10.320
[VLADIMIR] Yes.

1167
01:33:12.840 --> 01:33:14.540
[SLOW SINISTER MUSIC PLAYING]

1168
01:33:40.780 --> 01:33:43.270
[CHEWING LOUDLY]

1169
01:33:44.040 --> 01:33:45.490
I said I'd set her free.

1170
01:33:46.580 --> 01:33:47.820
That you could join her.

1171
01:33:50.750 --> 01:33:52.080
[DR. YUEH GRUNTS]

1172
01:33:52.710 --> 01:33:53.830
So. join her.

1173
01:33:54.630 --> 01:33:55.960
- [KNIFE SLICES]
- [BODY THUDS]

1174
01:34:03.560 --> 01:34:05.050
What do you think is next?

1175
01:34:09.520 --> 01:34:10.630
[PAUL] It's a thumper.

1176
01:34:11.600 --> 01:34:12.690
No stillsuits.

1177
01:34:13.360 --> 01:34:14.940
The one thing we actually need.

1178
01:34:20.320 --> 01:34:23.150
For hundreds of years.
we've traded blood for blood.

1179
01:34:24.830 --> 01:34:25.860
But no more.

1180
01:34:28.410 --> 01:34:31.120
Your son is dead.
Your concubine is dead.

1181
01:34:32.420 --> 01:34:34.750
Tonight the House of Atreides falls.

1182
01:34:37.960 --> 01:34:40.170
And your bloodline ends forever.

1183
01:34:42.760 --> 01:34:44.050
[LETO MUMBLING]

1184
01:34:54.230 --> 01:34:55.220
What did you say?

1185
01:35:05.240 --> 01:35:06.610
[SOFTLY] Here I am...

1186
01:35:08.160 --> 01:35:09.570
<i>here I remain.</i>

1187
01:35:11.410 --> 01:35:12.450
[TOOTH CRUNCHES]

1188
01:35:12.960 --> 01:35:14.070
[EXHALES FORCEFULLY]

1189
01:35:14.670 --> 01:35:16.280
- [GASPING]
- [DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

1190
01:35:19.340 --> 01:35:20.420
[PITER COUGHS]

1191
01:35:39.360 --> 01:35:40.470
[CRIES SOFTLY]

1192
01:36:01.050 --> 01:36:02.540
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

1193
01:36:22.280 --> 01:36:24.140
[DRAMATIC LAMENTATION MUSIC PLAYING]

1194
01:36:37.750 --> 01:36:38.870
[ENGINE ROARING IN DISTANCE]

1195
01:36:52.970 --> 01:36:53.960
[DUNCAN] Kynes!

1196
01:36:55.810 --> 01:36:57.350
It's not safe for you here.

1197
01:36:57.520 --> 01:36:58.640
[DUNCAN] Will you tell
the Great Houses

1198
01:36:58.730 --> 01:37:00.220
of the Landsraad
how we were betrayed?

1199
01:37:00.820 --> 01:37:02.310
How the best of them were murdered?

1200
01:37:03.320 --> 01:37:05.310
I am commanded to say nothing.

1201
01:37:06.900 --> 01:37:08.240
To see nothing.

1202
01:37:10.450 --> 01:37:12.070
The Emperor sent us here to die.

1203
01:37:12.660 --> 01:37:14.150
[LAMENTATION MUSIC CONTINUES]

1204
01:37:37.060 --> 01:37:38.270
[MAN CHOKING]

1205
01:37:41.610 --> 01:37:43.060
[STRAINED BREATHING]

1206
01:37:58.250 --> 01:37:59.410
[COUGHING]

1207
01:38:01.250 --> 01:38:02.540
[PAUL] There's spice in the tent.

1208
01:38:11.390 --> 01:38:12.590
[COUGHING]

1209
01:38:13.970 --> 01:38:15.050
[CLEARS THROAT]

1210
01:38:23.940 --> 01:38:25.350
[SLOW DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

1211
01:38:36.040 --> 01:38:37.450
[VOICES WHISPERING INDISTINCTLY]

1212
01:38:50.130 --> 01:38:51.590
[SOLDIERS CLAMORING]

1213
01:39:14.120 --> 01:39:15.530
[PANTING]

1214
01:39:18.830 --> 01:39:20.690
[SLOW OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

1215
01:39:29.260 --> 01:39:31.120
That's the future. It's coming.

1216
01:39:35.850 --> 01:39:37.300
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

1217
01:39:46.610 --> 01:39:48.560
Holy war spreading across the universe

1218
01:39:48.650 --> 01:39:50.010
like unquenchable fire.

1219
01:39:51.030 --> 01:39:52.110
[VOICES CONTINUE WHISPERING]

1220
01:40:01.790 --> 01:40:02.900
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

1221
01:40:03.120 --> 01:40:04.910
Paul. you're scared. I can see it.

1222
01:40:06.080 --> 01:40:07.670
Tell me. please. what do you fear?

1223
01:40:09.250 --> 01:40:10.580
[VOICES CONTINUE WHISPERING]

1224
01:40:18.350 --> 01:40:20.210
Somebody help me. please.

1225
01:40:21.270 --> 01:40:22.430
Paul.

1226
01:40:24.730 --> 01:40:25.720
It's coming.

1227
01:40:26.600 --> 01:40:28.060
<i>I see a holy war spreading</i>

1228
01:40:28.150 --> 01:40:29.810
<i>across the universe
like unquenchable fire.</i>

1229
01:40:30.360 --> 01:40:33.070
A warrior religion
that waves the Atreides banner

1230
01:40:33.150 --> 01:40:34.270
in my father's name.

1231
01:40:34.360 --> 01:40:35.350
[LADY JESSICA] Paul.

1232
01:40:35.450 --> 01:40:36.980
Fanatical legions worshipping

1233
01:40:37.370 --> 01:40:38.900
<i>at the shrine of my father's skull.</i>

1234
01:40:40.160 --> 01:40:41.990
<i>A war in my name!</i>

1235
01:40:42.830 --> 01:40:44.440
Everyone's shouting my name!

1236
01:40:44.580 --> 01:40:45.570
Paul.

1237
01:40:49.250 --> 01:40:50.620
Paul Atreides.

1238
01:40:51.590 --> 01:40:54.420
You are your father's son.
You are my son.

1239
01:40:54.590 --> 01:40:57.050
You are the Duke Paul Atreides.

1240
01:40:58.220 --> 01:41:00.960
You know who you are.
You know who you are.

1241
01:41:01.060 --> 01:41:02.050
[DISTORTED VOICE] Get off me!

1242
01:41:04.140 --> 01:41:05.470
[NORMAL VOICE] You did this to me!

1243
01:41:05.850 --> 01:41:08.090
You Bene Gesserit made me a freak!

1244
01:41:15.860 --> 01:41:17.570
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

1245
01:41:26.460 --> 01:41:28.040
[PAUL CRYING]

1246
01:41:33.590 --> 01:41:35.040
My father is dead.

1247
01:41:36.090 --> 01:41:37.460
[PAUL SOBBING]

1248
01:41:43.260 --> 01:41:45.010
[MOURNFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

1249
01:42:07.460 --> 01:42:08.990
[DEVICE BEEPING]

1250
01:42:12.460 --> 01:42:13.830
[PAUL SOFTLY] Someone's near.

1251
01:42:14.840 --> 01:42:16.250
You need to drink.

1252
01:42:18.050 --> 01:42:19.880
It's recycled water from the tent.

1253
01:42:28.140 --> 01:42:29.470
Sweat and tears.

1254
01:42:33.520 --> 01:42:34.850
All right. let's get out of here.

1255
01:42:38.940 --> 01:42:40.430
[DEVICE WHIRRING]

1256
01:42:42.160 --> 01:42:43.520
[SHIELD BUZZING]

1257
01:42:54.210 --> 01:42:55.420
[SHIELD BUZZING]

1258
01:43:00.510 --> 01:43:01.870
[SQUEAKS]

1259
01:43:05.180 --> 01:43:06.670
[WHIMPERS]

1260
01:43:10.890 --> 01:43:12.680
[MUFFLED WHIRRING]

1261
01:43:17.480 --> 01:43:19.020
[GRUNTING AND PANTING]

1262
01:43:28.410 --> 01:43:29.570
[SQUEAKS]

1263
01:43:33.120 --> 01:43:34.410
[PAUL GRUNTS]

1264
01:43:35.710 --> 01:43:36.790
[LADY JESSICA PANTING]

1265
01:43:39.630 --> 01:43:40.750
[ENGINE ROARING]

1266
01:43:48.680 --> 01:43:49.800
That's Duncan.

1267
01:43:59.190 --> 01:44:00.230
[PANTING]

1268
01:44:00.320 --> 01:44:01.480
My lady.

1269
01:44:01.650 --> 01:44:02.640
Paul.

1270
01:44:03.400 --> 01:44:05.190
I'm so sorry. Your father...

1271
01:44:05.570 --> 01:44:06.690
We know.

1272
01:44:08.740 --> 01:44:09.900
My lord Duke.

1273
01:44:23.510 --> 01:44:24.500
Here.

1274
01:44:26.640 --> 01:44:27.720
Drink this.

1275
01:44:35.600 --> 01:44:37.310
[DUNCAN] Harkonnens hit
every population center

1276
01:44:37.400 --> 01:44:38.730
on the planet at once.

1277
01:44:39.150 --> 01:44:41.560
There must have been
10 legions. hundreds of ships.

1278
01:44:41.730 --> 01:44:42.970
There were Sardaukar with them.

1279
01:44:43.860 --> 01:44:45.770
- At least two battalions.
- What? Are you sure?

1280
01:44:46.450 --> 01:44:48.110
You cross swords with a Sardaukar.

1281
01:44:49.120 --> 01:44:50.110
you know it.

1282
01:44:50.620 --> 01:44:53.660
[LADY JESSICA SIGHS]
So. the Emperor's taken a side.

1283
01:44:55.500 --> 01:44:57.160
What says
the Judge of the Change?

1284
01:44:58.830 --> 01:45:00.750
The Emperor forbids me
from saying anything at all.

1285
01:45:00.920 --> 01:45:02.660
And yet you risk your life
to help us.

1286
01:45:11.180 --> 01:45:12.420
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

1287
01:45:17.560 --> 01:45:19.020
[MAN SHOUTING]

1288
01:45:21.360 --> 01:45:23.140
- [THUNDER CONTINUES RUMBLING]
- [CLAMORING]

1289
01:45:23.230 --> 01:45:24.520
[WORKER] Storm's coming.

1290
01:45:28.070 --> 01:45:29.360
[WORKERS SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

1291
01:45:39.000 --> 01:45:40.960
[DR. KYNES] The storm
will be here in a few hours.

1292
01:45:41.130 --> 01:45:42.210
We'll be safe here.

1293
01:45:43.920 --> 01:45:45.500
Do you know what this place is?

1294
01:45:46.260 --> 01:45:48.500
It's an old ecological testing station.

1295
01:45:52.050 --> 01:45:53.800
They were meant to tame the planet.

1296
01:45:53.970 --> 01:45:55.880
Free the water locked beneath the sands.

1297
01:45:59.480 --> 01:46:01.390
Arrakis could have been a paradise.

1298
01:46:02.150 --> 01:46:04.940
The work had begun.
but then the spice was discovered.

1299
01:46:05.110 --> 01:46:07.320
And suddenly no one
wanted the desert to go away.

1300
01:46:07.990 --> 01:46:08.980
Tanat.

1301
01:46:09.070 --> 01:46:10.900
will you find stillsuits
to fit our visitors?

1302
01:46:10.990 --> 01:46:12.110
[TANAT] Yes. Liet.

1303
01:46:12.280 --> 01:46:13.650
[DR. KYNES] Shamir.
a coffee service. please.

1304
01:46:13.830 --> 01:46:14.990
[SHAMIR] Of course. Liet.

1305
01:46:16.370 --> 01:46:18.490
- [DOOR UNLOCKS]
- Who are you to the Fremen?

1306
01:46:45.150 --> 01:46:46.890
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1307
01:46:56.950 --> 01:46:58.440
[WIND HOWLING]

1308
01:47:09.720 --> 01:47:11.170
[PAUL] You know what
the Great Houses fear most.

1309
01:47:11.260 --> 01:47:12.340
Dr. Kynes?

1310
01:47:14.430 --> 01:47:16.090
Exactly what has happened
to us here.

1311
01:47:17.600 --> 01:47:18.710
The Sardaukar coming

1312
01:47:18.810 --> 01:47:20.220
and picking them off
one by one.

1313
01:47:23.650 --> 01:47:25.140
Only together
can they stand a chance

1314
01:47:25.230 --> 01:47:26.270
against the Imperium.

1315
01:47:28.780 --> 01:47:30.020
Would you bear witness?

1316
01:47:31.150 --> 01:47:33.360
Testify that the Emperor
has moved against us here?

1317
01:47:34.240 --> 01:47:36.070
If they believe me.

1318
01:47:37.280 --> 01:47:38.990
there would be general warfare

1319
01:47:39.080 --> 01:47:41.070
between the Great Houses
and the Emperor.

1320
01:47:41.250 --> 01:47:42.360
Chaos

1321
01:47:42.960 --> 01:47:44.290
across the Imperium.

1322
01:47:44.580 --> 01:47:45.990
Suppose I presented the Emperor

1323
01:47:46.090 --> 01:47:47.330
with an alternative to chaos.

1324
01:47:48.590 --> 01:47:50.120
The Emperor has no sons.

1325
01:47:50.670 --> 01:47:52.080
And his daughters have yet to marry.

1326
01:47:52.720 --> 01:47:54.670
You'd make a play for the throne?

1327
01:47:55.640 --> 01:47:57.380
The Emperor feared the Atreides.

1328
01:47:57.470 --> 01:47:58.960
He brought you here to kill you.

1329
01:47:59.140 --> 01:48:00.720
What don't you understand?

1330
01:48:01.730 --> 01:48:04.390
You're a lost boy hiding
in a hole in the ground.

1331
01:48:09.270 --> 01:48:11.690
The Fremen speak
of the <i>Lisan al-Gaib.</i>

1332
01:48:12.700 --> 01:48:13.940
Careful.

1333
01:48:14.740 --> 01:48:17.530
The Voice from the Outer World
who will lead them to paradise.

1334
01:48:19.410 --> 01:48:20.570
Superstition.

1335
01:48:25.500 --> 01:48:27.210
I know you loved a Fremen warrior

1336
01:48:27.290 --> 01:48:28.500
and lost him in battle.

1337
01:48:31.960 --> 01:48:35.130
I know you walk in two worlds
and are known by many names.

1338
01:48:40.760 --> 01:48:42.220
I've seen your dream.

1339
01:48:46.900 --> 01:48:47.980
As emperor. Dr. Kynes.

1340
01:48:48.150 --> 01:48:49.980
I could make a paradise of Arrakis

1341
01:48:50.070 --> 01:48:51.310
with a wave of my hand.

1342
01:48:53.110 --> 01:48:54.100
[MAN SPEAKING CHAKOBSA]

1343
01:49:01.240 --> 01:49:02.230
[MAN 2 SHUSHING]

1344
01:49:39.620 --> 01:49:41.360
[SOLDIER SPEAKING SARDAUKAR]

1345
01:49:42.370 --> 01:49:44.150
- [EXPLOSIONS]
- [ALL GRUNTING]

1346
01:49:45.290 --> 01:49:46.820
- [BLADES SLICING]
- [GROANING]

1347
01:49:55.920 --> 01:49:57.580
[MUFFLED THUDDING]

1348
01:50:00.010 --> 01:50:01.670
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

1349
01:50:47.520 --> 01:50:48.470
Sardaukar!

1350
01:50:51.690 --> 01:50:52.850
No! Duncan!

1351
01:50:53.020 --> 01:50:54.140
[LADY JESSICA] Paul. no!

1352
01:50:54.310 --> 01:50:55.550
- [PAUL] Duncan. no!
- [LADY JESSICA] No!

1353
01:50:56.860 --> 01:50:58.020
- [PAUL] No!
- [LADY JESSICA] Paul. no!

1354
01:50:59.280 --> 01:51:00.440
[PAUL] Duncan. no!

1355
01:51:00.820 --> 01:51:03.060
- He's locked the door.
- [PAUL] Duncan! No!

1356
01:51:06.370 --> 01:51:07.530
[SLOW CHORAL MUSIC PLAYING]

1357
01:51:12.880 --> 01:51:14.410
[ALL GRUNTING]

1358
01:51:16.920 --> 01:51:18.210
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

1359
01:51:34.770 --> 01:51:35.760
[DUNCAN GROANS]

1360
01:51:42.070 --> 01:51:43.310
[SOLDIER SPEAKS SARDAUKAR]

1361
01:51:43.410 --> 01:51:44.940
[SHIELD CRACKLING]

1362
01:51:52.290 --> 01:51:53.250
He's gone.

1363
01:51:54.000 --> 01:51:54.990
[PAUL] Duncan!

1364
01:51:55.170 --> 01:51:56.620
We have to go. We have no choice.

1365
01:51:56.880 --> 01:51:58.080
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

1366
01:52:02.840 --> 01:52:03.710
[LASER FIRING]

1367
01:52:04.340 --> 01:52:06.380
[LADY JESSICA] Paul. go! Paul!

1368
01:52:20.280 --> 01:52:21.640
[DUNCAN YELLING]

1369
01:52:25.740 --> 01:52:27.280
[DR. KYNES] Come on.
Come on. come on!

1370
01:52:39.920 --> 01:52:41.460
[SHIELD BUZZING]

1371
01:52:48.720 --> 01:52:50.130
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

1372
01:52:58.690 --> 01:53:00.050
[PANTING] Follow the light.

1373
01:53:00.520 --> 01:53:02.230
You'll find a thopter ready to fly.

1374
01:53:02.820 --> 01:53:04.600
That storm out there is your best shot.

1375
01:53:05.030 --> 01:53:07.360
Above 5.000 meters. it's mostly dust.

1376
01:53:07.740 --> 01:53:11.320
Climb into it. Stay on top.
Head south. Find the Fremen.

1377
01:53:11.620 --> 01:53:12.610
Are you not coming with us?

1378
01:53:12.910 --> 01:53:13.950
It only seats two.

1379
01:53:14.200 --> 01:53:15.660
I'll go to the next station

1380
01:53:16.080 --> 01:53:17.620
and report this attack
to the Landsraad.

1381
01:53:17.790 --> 01:53:19.000
[LADY JESSICA] How?

1382
01:53:19.880 --> 01:53:20.870
I'm Fremen.

1383
01:53:21.840 --> 01:53:23.080
The desert's my home.

1384
01:53:24.090 --> 01:53:25.080
Good luck.

1385
01:53:25.260 --> 01:53:26.210
[PAUL] Good luck.

1386
01:53:33.640 --> 01:53:34.760
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

1387
01:54:24.360 --> 01:54:25.270
[SWITCHES CLICKING]

1388
01:54:26.360 --> 01:54:27.270
[ENGINE SPUTTERING]

1389
01:54:32.910 --> 01:54:33.900
[ENGINE RUMBLES]

1390
01:54:35.740 --> 01:54:36.780
[ENGINE STARTS]

1391
01:55:37.510 --> 01:55:38.500
[BLADE STABS]

1392
01:55:40.560 --> 01:55:41.720
- [BLADE RETRACTS]
- [GROANS]

1393
01:55:42.690 --> 01:55:44.890
[DRAMATIC LAMENTATION
MUSIC PLAYING]

1394
01:56:03.370 --> 01:56:04.360
[ASSASSIN SPEAKING SARDAUKAR]

1395
01:56:07.540 --> 01:56:09.460
[IN ENGLISH] I serve only one master.

1396
01:56:10.300 --> 01:56:13.090
His name is <i>Shai-Hulud.</i>

1397
01:56:14.680 --> 01:56:16.790
[POUNDING RHYTHMICALLY]

1398
01:56:17.260 --> 01:56:18.250
[SPEAKS SARDAUKAR]

1399
01:56:19.470 --> 01:56:20.510
[ASSASSIN GRUNTS]

1400
01:56:21.600 --> 01:56:24.010
[ASSASSINS GRUNTING]

1401
01:56:27.560 --> 01:56:28.550
[GRUNTS]

1402
01:56:33.150 --> 01:56:34.390
[PANICKED CHATTER]

1403
01:56:35.030 --> 01:56:37.400
- [SANDWORM ROARS]
- [ASSASSINS SCREAMING]

1404
01:56:50.630 --> 01:56:51.710
[SWITCHES CLICK]

1405
01:56:55.590 --> 01:56:57.050
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

1406
01:56:58.470 --> 01:56:59.880
There are jet flares behind us.

1407
01:57:10.020 --> 01:57:11.010
[LADY JESSICA GRUNTING]

1408
01:57:25.660 --> 01:57:26.870
[ALARM WAILING]

1409
01:57:31.920 --> 01:57:33.000
[ENGINE ACCELERATING]

1410
01:57:34.130 --> 01:57:35.870
Paul. We're not high enough!

1411
01:57:42.470 --> 01:57:43.550
[MISSILE WHISTLING]

1412
01:57:45.890 --> 01:57:46.880
- [METAL RATTLING]
- [EXPLOSION]

1413
01:57:50.770 --> 01:57:52.230
- [METALLIC CLANKING]
- [PAUL GASPS]

1414
01:57:57.740 --> 01:58:00.820
- [CLANKING CONTINUES]
- [METAL SQUEAKS]

1415
01:58:01.780 --> 01:58:02.820
[ENGINE RUMBLING]

1416
01:58:05.120 --> 01:58:06.080
[METAL RATTLING]

1417
01:58:08.370 --> 01:58:09.450
I must not fear.

1418
01:58:10.040 --> 01:58:11.200
Fear is the mind-killer.

1419
01:58:11.920 --> 01:58:14.790
Fear is the little death
that brings obliteration.

1420
01:58:15.710 --> 01:58:17.000
[RUMBLING AND CLANKING STOP]

1421
01:58:21.090 --> 01:58:23.590
[VOICES WHISPERING] <i>See the friend.</i>

1422
01:58:28.020 --> 01:58:30.060
<i>See the friend.</i>

1423
01:58:33.570 --> 01:58:35.980
[JAMIS] <i>The mystery of life
isn't a problem to solve...</i>

1424
01:58:39.610 --> 01:58:41.350
<i>but a reality to experience.</i>

1425
01:58:45.410 --> 01:58:46.950
A process that cannot
be understood

1426
01:58:47.040 --> 01:58:48.240
by stopping it.

1427
01:58:49.960 --> 01:58:51.740
We must move
with the flow of the process.

1428
01:58:53.340 --> 01:58:54.500
<i>We must join it.</i>

1429
01:58:55.920 --> 01:58:56.910
<i>We must flow with it.</i>

1430
01:58:57.420 --> 01:58:58.660
[VOICES] <i>Let go.</i>

1431
01:58:59.010 --> 01:59:00.340
<i>Let go.</i>

1432
01:59:02.840 --> 01:59:03.830
[SWITCHES CLICK]

1433
01:59:04.050 --> 01:59:05.170
[ENGINE HUMMING]

1434
01:59:29.290 --> 01:59:30.450
[BUBBLING]

1435
01:59:34.130 --> 01:59:35.120
[SERVANT SPEAKING HARKONNEN]

1436
01:59:44.510 --> 01:59:47.170
- [WATER BUBBLING]
- [BREATHES HEAVILY]

1437
01:59:48.430 --> 01:59:51.720
[IN ENGLISH] We chased them
into a Coriolis storm.

1438
01:59:53.730 --> 01:59:55.810
Winds at 800 kilometers an hour.

1439
02:00:01.110 --> 02:00:02.650
Nothing survives such a storm.

1440
02:00:03.360 --> 02:00:04.270
They're dead.

1441
02:00:06.240 --> 02:00:07.320
It's a certainty.

1442
02:00:12.620 --> 02:00:13.580
[GRUNTS]

1443
02:00:15.040 --> 02:00:16.750
So. it's done. Finally.

1444
02:00:19.630 --> 02:00:21.120
Send word to Giedi Prime

1445
02:00:21.590 --> 02:00:23.580
to begin selling our spice reserves.

1446
02:00:25.180 --> 02:00:26.130
But slowly.

1447
02:00:27.510 --> 02:00:28.970
We don't want the price to fall.

1448
02:00:30.100 --> 02:00:31.460
You have no idea how much it cost me

1449
02:00:31.560 --> 02:00:33.340
to bring such a force to bear here.

1450
02:00:34.390 --> 02:00:36.060
Now I only have one requirement.

1451
02:00:37.190 --> 02:00:38.270
Income.

1452
02:00:39.320 --> 02:00:40.680
So. squeeze. Rabban.

1453
02:00:41.820 --> 02:00:42.980
Squeeze hard.

1454
02:00:43.360 --> 02:00:44.400
Yes. Uncle.

1455
02:00:46.320 --> 02:00:47.400
And the Fremen?

1456
02:00:48.580 --> 02:00:49.660
Kill them all.

1457
02:00:54.160 --> 02:00:55.280
[WIND GUSTING]

1458
02:01:05.800 --> 02:01:06.710
[ALARM BEEPING RAPIDLY]

1459
02:01:13.350 --> 02:01:14.710
[PAUL] We're above 5.000 meters.

1460
02:01:23.070 --> 02:01:24.020
[ENGINE ROARS]

1461
02:01:27.030 --> 02:01:27.860
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

1462
02:01:34.620 --> 02:01:35.660
[ORNITHOPTER RATTLING]

1463
02:01:35.750 --> 02:01:36.910
[PAUL GRUNTING]

1464
02:01:47.380 --> 02:01:48.540
[ENGINE ROARING]

1465
02:01:50.010 --> 02:01:51.380
[ALARM BEEPING RAPIDLY]

1466
02:01:53.770 --> 02:01:54.760
[SPUTTERING]

1467
02:01:56.020 --> 02:01:57.100
- [METALLIC RATTLING]
- [GASPING]

1468
02:01:57.640 --> 02:01:58.630
[GASPS]

1469
02:01:59.560 --> 02:02:00.800
[ALARM CONTINUES BEEPING]

1470
02:02:01.650 --> 02:02:02.640
[SWITCHES CLICK]

1471
02:02:02.730 --> 02:02:03.940
[ALARM STOPS BEEPING]

1472
02:02:09.160 --> 02:02:10.240
[SOFT RATTLING]

1473
02:02:17.540 --> 02:02:18.620
[WIND WHISTLING]

1474
02:02:23.210 --> 02:02:24.170
[RATTLING]

1475
02:02:27.170 --> 02:02:28.710
[BOTH GASPING]

1476
02:02:31.930 --> 02:02:33.130
[ENGINE WHINES]

1477
02:02:52.950 --> 02:02:54.690
[PAUL] As soon as we land.
run for the rocks.

1478
02:03:05.840 --> 02:03:07.290
[ENGINE ACCELERATES]

1479
02:03:09.130 --> 02:03:10.250
[LADY JESSICA WHIMPERING]

1480
02:03:16.600 --> 02:03:17.630
[ENGINE ROARING]

1481
02:04:00.180 --> 02:04:01.800
[BOTH PANTING]

1482
02:04:47.810 --> 02:04:49.020
And breathe through this.

1483
02:05:04.080 --> 02:05:05.240
[RUMBLING]

1484
02:05:20.050 --> 02:05:21.640
[PAUL OVER MASK]
Now we have to find the Fremen.

1485
02:05:23.600 --> 02:05:24.760
Are you good?

1486
02:05:24.930 --> 02:05:25.840
[LADY JESSICA] Yeah.

1487
02:05:26.480 --> 02:05:28.180
[SLOW SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

1488
02:06:33.170 --> 02:06:34.500
[VOICES ECHOING] <i>Paul...</i>

1489
02:06:41.470 --> 02:06:44.210
<i>Don't be frightened.</i>

1490
02:06:45.850 --> 02:06:48.510
[GIRL] <i>Even a little
desert mouse can survive.</i>

1491
02:06:49.640 --> 02:06:52.850
<i>[VOICES] Don't be frightened.</i>

1492
02:06:53.270 --> 02:06:54.640
[GIRL] <i>You'll need to face your fears.</i>

1493
02:06:55.020 --> 02:06:56.230
<i>[VOICES] A friend...</i>

1494
02:06:56.860 --> 02:06:59.400
<i>A friend will help you.</i>

1495
02:07:01.360 --> 02:07:02.730
<i>Follow the friend.</i>

1496
02:07:06.120 --> 02:07:07.110
[JAMIS] <i>You have much to learn.</i>

1497
02:07:09.580 --> 02:07:11.410
And I will show you
the ways of the desert.

1498
02:07:15.460 --> 02:07:16.540
Come with me.

1499
02:07:23.090 --> 02:07:24.580
[MYSTERIOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

1500
02:07:45.030 --> 02:07:47.320
[PAUL] The <i>sietch</i> where Duncan lived

1501
02:07:48.700 --> 02:07:49.860
is somewhere off that way.

1502
02:07:53.170 --> 02:07:54.780
[LADY JESSICA] I can see
greenery over there.

1503
02:07:56.040 --> 02:07:56.910
There.

1504
02:07:57.090 --> 02:07:58.420
[PAUL] That means Fremen live there.

1505
02:08:03.680 --> 02:08:04.880
We'll cross after dark.

1506
02:08:05.970 --> 02:08:07.090
That's how the Fremen do it.

1507
02:08:10.890 --> 02:08:12.680
[PAUL] We're about to enter
worm territory.

1508
02:08:13.560 --> 02:08:15.140
We can't walk like regular humans.

1509
02:08:15.520 --> 02:08:16.480
If we do. we're dead.

1510
02:08:16.980 --> 02:08:18.470
We'll have to walk like the Fremen do.

1511
02:08:18.860 --> 02:08:20.060
It's called a sandwalk.

1512
02:08:20.650 --> 02:08:22.480
At least according
to the filmbooks back home.

1513
02:08:23.320 --> 02:08:24.560
[LADY JESSICA] Yeah. Yeah. okay.

1514
02:08:24.740 --> 02:08:26.030
[PAUL] Okay. Follow me.

1515
02:08:26.370 --> 02:08:27.610
Do the same moves.

1516
02:08:39.380 --> 02:08:40.490
[COMPASS TICKING]

1517
02:08:41.590 --> 02:08:42.830
I think this is the right direction.

1518
02:09:03.030 --> 02:09:04.610
[BOTH GRUNTING]

1519
02:09:17.580 --> 02:09:18.950
[PANTING]

1520
02:09:28.180 --> 02:09:29.510
[DISTANT RUMBLING]

1521
02:09:39.060 --> 02:09:40.140
[RUMBLING FADES]

1522
02:10:05.510 --> 02:10:06.500
[PAUL] It's close by.

1523
02:10:07.470 --> 02:10:08.670
Let's get out of here.

1524
02:10:10.220 --> 02:10:11.840
- [THUD]
- Wait.

1525
02:10:13.260 --> 02:10:15.010
- [HOLLOW THUDDING]
- It's drum sand.

1526
02:10:15.350 --> 02:10:16.340
[WIND GUSTING]

1527
02:10:19.690 --> 02:10:20.800
- [GASPS]
- [PAUL] Run.

1528
02:10:21.690 --> 02:10:22.800
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

1529
02:10:27.610 --> 02:10:28.900
[LADY JESSICA] Go! Go!

1530
02:10:38.160 --> 02:10:39.280
[GRUNTS]

1531
02:10:40.080 --> 02:10:41.740
[WHIMPERING]

1532
02:11:04.190 --> 02:11:05.400
[RUMBLING STOPS]

1533
02:11:10.070 --> 02:11:11.400
[PANTING]

1534
02:11:13.410 --> 02:11:14.740
[SANDWORM MOANS]

1535
02:11:16.370 --> 02:11:17.660
[GASPING]

1536
02:11:30.630 --> 02:11:32.340
[RHYTHMIC THUMPING]

1537
02:11:33.510 --> 02:11:34.500
[THUMPING STOPS]

1538
02:11:38.430 --> 02:11:40.890
[SOFT RHYTHMIC THUMPING]

1539
02:11:41.140 --> 02:11:42.180
[PAUL] It's a thumper.

1540
02:11:47.860 --> 02:11:49.140
Someone set off a thumper.

1541
02:11:51.610 --> 02:11:52.690
[THUMPING FADES]

1542
02:11:55.490 --> 02:11:57.280
[RHYTHMIC THUMPING]

1543
02:11:58.330 --> 02:11:59.410
[THUMPING STOPS]

1544
02:12:04.130 --> 02:12:06.120
[LADY JESSICA] Paul! Run!

1545
02:12:17.890 --> 02:12:19.220
[BOTH PANTING]

1546
02:12:21.230 --> 02:12:22.180
How big are they?

1547
02:12:22.440 --> 02:12:23.520
That was insane.

1548
02:12:26.860 --> 02:12:27.720
[GROANS]

1549
02:12:28.570 --> 02:12:29.480
Someone called it.

1550
02:12:32.490 --> 02:12:33.400
[LADY JESSICA PANTS]

1551
02:12:39.120 --> 02:12:40.070
[IN SIGN LANGUAGE]

1552
02:12:46.290 --> 02:12:47.280
[PEBBLE CLATTERS]

1553
02:12:52.380 --> 02:12:53.500
[FOOTSTEPS]

1554
02:13:02.350 --> 02:13:03.590
[STILGAR OVER MASK] <i>Do not run.</i>

1555
02:13:05.060 --> 02:13:07.350
<i>You will only waste
your body's water.</i>

1556
02:13:08.520 --> 02:13:09.390
<i>Hold.</i>

1557
02:13:17.200 --> 02:13:18.190
Stilgar.

1558
02:13:18.280 --> 02:13:19.270
- [BLADE RUSTLES]
- Hey!

1559
02:13:19.910 --> 02:13:21.240
You know me. I was there

1560
02:13:21.330 --> 02:13:22.530
when you came
to my father's Council.

1561
02:13:22.830 --> 02:13:23.690
[STILGAR] Oh.

1562
02:13:24.000 --> 02:13:25.530
This is the Duke's son.

1563
02:13:26.210 --> 02:13:27.200
[JAMIS] Why are you waiting?

1564
02:13:27.960 --> 02:13:29.040
We need their water.

1565
02:13:30.000 --> 02:13:31.710
[STILGAR] This is the boy
I told you about.

1566
02:13:32.250 --> 02:13:33.420
We can't touch him.

1567
02:13:33.510 --> 02:13:34.420
[WOMAN SPEAKING FREMEN]

1568
02:13:37.970 --> 02:13:39.130
[JAMIS IN ENGLISH] They are weaklings.

1569
02:13:39.300 --> 02:13:40.130
[STILGAR] Jamis.

1570
02:13:41.220 --> 02:13:43.090
That was a brave crossing they made

1571
02:13:43.180 --> 02:13:44.800
in the path of <i>Shai-Hulud.</i>

1572
02:13:46.190 --> 02:13:48.550
He does not speak
or act like a weakling.

1573
02:13:50.270 --> 02:13:51.480
Nor did his father.

1574
02:13:52.150 --> 02:13:53.440
[JAMIS] My thumper saved his life.

1575
02:13:54.820 --> 02:13:56.480
Go back to reason. Stilgar.

1576
02:13:57.280 --> 02:13:58.310
He's not The One.

1577
02:14:00.660 --> 02:14:01.650
[SIGHS]

1578
02:14:01.740 --> 02:14:03.030
We have powerful friends.

1579
02:14:03.620 --> 02:14:06.240
You help us off-world. to Caladan.

1580
02:14:06.830 --> 02:14:08.040
you will be well rewarded.

1581
02:14:08.210 --> 02:14:10.570
What wealth can you offer
beyond the water

1582
02:14:10.960 --> 02:14:12.040
in your flesh?

1583
02:14:15.300 --> 02:14:16.380
[STILGAR] Hmm...

1584
02:14:17.420 --> 02:14:18.540
The boy is young.

1585
02:14:19.180 --> 02:14:20.670
He can learn our ways.

1586
02:14:21.470 --> 02:14:22.800
He may have sanctuary.

1587
02:14:24.220 --> 02:14:26.430
But the woman is untrained...

1588
02:14:29.190 --> 02:14:30.520
and too old to learn.

1589
02:14:34.360 --> 02:14:35.720
[LOW TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

1590
02:14:43.240 --> 02:14:44.400
[SNIFFLES]

1591
02:14:49.620 --> 02:14:50.830
[GRUNTING]

1592
02:14:56.920 --> 02:14:57.910
[GROANS]

1593
02:15:01.970 --> 02:15:03.880
- [BOTH GRUNT]
- [STILGAR] Back. you dogs.

1594
02:15:05.600 --> 02:15:06.760
She'll cut my throat.

1595
02:15:12.900 --> 02:15:15.140
Why didn't you say
you were a weirding woman?

1596
02:15:15.610 --> 02:15:16.560
And a fighter?

1597
02:15:17.110 --> 02:15:18.570
Conversation ran short.

1598
02:15:19.360 --> 02:15:20.940
[STILGAR] Peace. woman.

1599
02:15:21.570 --> 02:15:22.690
Peace.

1600
02:15:23.740 --> 02:15:25.230
I judged hastily.

1601
02:15:29.330 --> 02:15:30.410
[SNIFFS]

1602
02:15:31.620 --> 02:15:32.830
[STILGAR GRUNTS]

1603
02:15:33.290 --> 02:15:34.280
[SPEAKING CHAKOBSA]

1604
02:16:04.950 --> 02:16:06.860
[GIRL IN ENGLISH] <i>I would not
have let you hurt my friends.</i>

1605
02:16:32.390 --> 02:16:33.720
They say you're the <i>Mahdi.</i>

1606
02:16:35.100 --> 02:16:36.640
But you look like a little boy.

1607
02:16:38.270 --> 02:16:39.560
You chose the hardest way up.

1608
02:16:39.900 --> 02:16:40.770
Follow me.

1609
02:16:43.610 --> 02:16:44.600
[STILGAR SPEAKING CHAKOBSA]

1610
02:16:48.580 --> 02:16:49.740
[IN ENGLISH] Give it to me.

1611
02:16:57.380 --> 02:16:58.790
You will have your own maula pistol

1612
02:16:58.880 --> 02:17:00.080
when you've earned it.

1613
02:17:00.960 --> 02:17:01.950
Give it to me.

1614
02:17:07.970 --> 02:17:09.800
Chani. take charge of the newcomers.

1615
02:17:10.180 --> 02:17:12.220
See that they are safe
on the journey. Let's go.

1616
02:17:12.640 --> 02:17:13.850
[JAMIS] I will not have them.

1617
02:17:20.900 --> 02:17:21.890
[STILGAR] Jamis.

1618
02:17:22.570 --> 02:17:24.610
I have spoken. Be still.

1619
02:17:24.900 --> 02:17:26.360
[JAMIS] You talk like a leader.

1620
02:17:27.780 --> 02:17:29.240
But the strongest leads.

1621
02:17:30.910 --> 02:17:32.020
She bested you.

1622
02:17:33.950 --> 02:17:35.160
I invoke the amtal.

1623
02:17:36.330 --> 02:17:38.620
[STILGAR] You may not challenge
a <i>Sayyadina.</i>

1624
02:17:38.790 --> 02:17:40.030
Then who will fight in her name?

1625
02:17:40.590 --> 02:17:42.370
Jamis. don't do this.

1626
02:17:43.300 --> 02:17:45.210
Don't. The night is fading.

1627
02:17:45.380 --> 02:17:47.920
Then the sun will witness this death.

1628
02:17:48.590 --> 02:17:49.830
Where is her champion?

1629
02:18:01.360 --> 02:18:02.720
I accept her champion.

1630
02:18:26.380 --> 02:18:28.040
[SLOW DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

1631
02:18:32.600 --> 02:18:33.760
[GRUNTING]

1632
02:18:35.430 --> 02:18:38.170
[VOICES] <i>Paul Atreides must die...</i>

1633
02:18:41.100 --> 02:18:45.560
<i>for</i> Kwisatz Haderach <i>to rise.</i>

1634
02:18:48.530 --> 02:18:51.320
<i>Don't be frightened.</i>

1635
02:18:52.320 --> 02:18:53.690
<i>Don't resist.</i>

1636
02:19:00.000 --> 02:19:01.960
<i>When you take a life.</i>

1637
02:19:03.000 --> 02:19:04.740
<i>you take your own.</i>

1638
02:19:12.550 --> 02:19:13.510
[MOANS]

1639
02:19:27.990 --> 02:19:29.150
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

1640
02:19:36.700 --> 02:19:38.360
I don't believe
you're the <i>Lisan al-Gaib.</i>

1641
02:19:40.620 --> 02:19:42.160
But I want you to die with honor.

1642
02:19:54.140 --> 02:19:56.500
This crysknife was given to me
by my great aunt.

1643
02:20:00.230 --> 02:20:02.060
It's made from a tooth of <i>Shai-Hulud.</i>

1644
02:20:02.690 --> 02:20:03.800
The great sandworm.

1645
02:20:06.020 --> 02:20:08.110
This will be a great honor.
for you to die holding it.

1646
02:20:13.240 --> 02:20:14.820
[JAMIS SHOUTS]
Where is the Outworlder?

1647
02:20:19.750 --> 02:20:21.080
Jamis is a good fighter.

1648
02:20:22.710 --> 02:20:23.740
He won't let you suffer.

1649
02:20:25.790 --> 02:20:26.870
Chani...

1650
02:20:30.340 --> 02:20:31.170
Um...

1651
02:20:37.140 --> 02:20:38.130
[SCOFFS]

1652
02:20:39.560 --> 02:20:40.420
Never mind.

1653
02:20:53.490 --> 02:20:54.980
[SLOW DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

1654
02:21:36.610 --> 02:21:37.900
May thy knife chip and shatter.

1655
02:21:46.250 --> 02:21:47.700
You should welcome my blade.

1656
02:21:51.630 --> 02:21:52.960
This world will kill you.

1657
02:21:56.720 --> 02:21:57.880
Quicker this way.

1658
02:22:05.600 --> 02:22:06.720
[SPECTATORS SPEAK CHAKOBSA IN UNISON]

1659
02:22:09.560 --> 02:22:10.970
- [MAN SPEAKS CHAKOBSA]
- [JAMIS GRUNTING]

1660
02:22:16.450 --> 02:22:17.860
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

1661
02:22:38.050 --> 02:22:39.630
- Do you yield?
- [SPECTATORS EXCLAIM]

1662
02:22:39.720 --> 02:22:41.930
[STILGAR SPEAKING CHAKOBSA]

1663
02:22:42.010 --> 02:22:43.630
[STILGAR IN ENGLISH]
The boy doesn't know our rule.

1664
02:22:43.720 --> 02:22:44.710
[YELLS]

1665
02:22:44.810 --> 02:22:46.640
There's no yielding
under the amtal rule.

1666
02:22:46.810 --> 02:22:48.300
Only death is the test of it.

1667
02:22:48.520 --> 02:22:49.470
[JAMIS YELLING]

1668
02:22:53.150 --> 02:22:54.600
[BOTH GRUNTING]

1669
02:22:56.900 --> 02:22:58.610
- Is he toying with him?
- No.

1670
02:23:00.450 --> 02:23:01.440
Paul has never killed a man.

1671
02:23:03.830 --> 02:23:04.990
[BOTH GRUNT]

1672
02:23:07.080 --> 02:23:08.040
[YELLING]

1673
02:23:10.460 --> 02:23:12.070
[DRAMATIC LAMENTATION MUSIC PLAYING]

1674
02:23:12.540 --> 02:23:16.500
[VOICES] Kwisatz Haderach.

1675
02:23:16.960 --> 02:23:18.040
[YELLING]

1676
02:23:19.970 --> 02:23:22.750
Kwisatz Haderach.

1677
02:23:23.140 --> 02:23:26.930
<i>Climb up. Rise.</i>

1678
02:23:28.850 --> 02:23:29.890
[STABS]

1679
02:23:30.600 --> 02:23:31.720
[GRUNTS]

1680
02:23:48.950 --> 02:23:50.290
[JAMIS GROANING]

1681
02:24:03.720 --> 02:24:05.710
[MOURNFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

1682
02:24:35.330 --> 02:24:37.070
[MOURNFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

1683
02:25:14.790 --> 02:25:16.080
[SPEAKING CHAKOBSA]

1684
02:25:19.840 --> 02:25:21.120
[IN ENGLISH] You're one of us now.

1685
02:25:21.710 --> 02:25:22.950
A life for a life.

1686
02:25:23.720 --> 02:25:25.250
Come with us to <i>Sietch</i> Tabr.

1687
02:25:25.510 --> 02:25:26.370
No.

1688
02:25:26.800 --> 02:25:27.960
Paul needs to get off-world.

1689
02:25:28.350 --> 02:25:30.260
You must have ways. You have smugglers.

1690
02:25:30.350 --> 02:25:31.380
you have ships.

1691
02:25:31.600 --> 02:25:32.760
- [PAUL] No.
- [LADY JESSICA] You have...

1692
02:25:33.930 --> 02:25:35.600
The Emperor sent us to this place.

1693
02:25:37.560 --> 02:25:38.770
And my father came.

1694
02:25:40.070 --> 02:25:41.400
not for spice.

1695
02:25:42.320 --> 02:25:43.600
not for the riches.

1696
02:25:45.030 --> 02:25:46.480
but for the strength of your people.

1697
02:25:50.160 --> 02:25:51.650
My road leads into the desert.

1698
02:25:54.910 --> 02:25:55.870
I can see it.

1699
02:25:58.630 --> 02:25:59.790
If you'll have us.

1700
02:26:01.340 --> 02:26:02.330
we will come.

1701
02:26:09.220 --> 02:26:10.460
[SLOW DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

1702
02:26:51.640 --> 02:26:52.630
Desert power.

1703
02:26:54.390 --> 02:26:55.630
This is only the beginning.

1703
02:26:56.305 --> 02:27:56.229
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
